  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Creation'
      title: The Creation
      number: 1
      content: "In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the earth was formless and empty, and darkness was over the face
        of the deep. And the Spirit of God was hovering over the surface of the waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be light!\u201D And there was light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And God saw the light, that it was good, and God caused there to
        be a separation between the light and between the darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And
        there was evening and there was morning, the first day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be a vaulted dome in the midst of the
        waters, and let it cause a separation between the waters.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So God made the vaulted dome, and he caused a separation between
        the waters which were under the vaulted dome and between the waters which
        were over the vaulted dome. And it was so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And God called the vaulted dome \u201Cheaven.\u201D And there was
        evening, and there was morning, a second day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the waters under heaven be gathered to one
        place, and let the dry ground appear.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And God called the dry ground \u201Cearth,\u201D and he called the
        collection of the waters \u201Cseas.\u201D And God saw that it was good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the earth produce green plants that will
        bear seed\u2014fruit trees bearing fruit in which there is seed\u2014according
        to its kind, on the earth.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the earth brought forth green plants bearing seed according to
        its kind, and trees bearing fruit in which there was seed according to its
        kind. And God saw that it was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, a third day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be lights in the vaulted dome of heaven
        to separate day from night, and let them be as signs and for appointed times,
        and for days and years, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and they shall be as lights in the vaulted dome of heaven to give
        light on the earth.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And God made two lights, the greater light to rule the day and the
        smaller light to rule the night, and the stars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And God placed them in the vaulted dome of heaven to give light on
        the earth '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and to rule over the day and over the night, and to separate light
        from darkness. And God saw that it was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, a fourth day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the waters swarm with swarms of living creatures,
        and let birds fly over the earth across the face of the vaulted dome of heaven.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So God created the great sea creatures and every living creature
        that moves, with which the waters swarm, according to their kind, and every
        bird with wings according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And God blessed them, saying, \u201CBe fruitful and multiply, and
        fill the waters in the seas, and let the birds multiply on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And there was evening, and there was morning, a fifth day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet the earth bring forth living creatures according
        to their kind: cattle and moving things, and wild animals according to their
        kind.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So God made wild animals according to their kind and the cattle according
        to their kind, and every creeping thing of the earth according to its kind.
        And God saw that it was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet us make humankind in our image and according
        to our likeness, and let them rule over the fish of the sea, and over the
        birds of heaven, and over the cattle, and over all the earth, and over every
        moving thing that moves upon the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So God created humankind in his image, in the likeness of God he
        created him, male and female he created them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And God blessed them, and God said to them, \u201CBe fruitful and
        multiply, and fill the earth and subdue it, and rule over the fish of the
        sea and the birds of heaven, and over every animal that moves upon the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And God said, \u201CLook\u2014I am giving to you every plant that
        bears seed which is on the face of the whole earth, and every kind of tree
        that bears fruit. They shall be yours as food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And to every kind of animal of the earth and to every bird of heaven,
        and to everything that moves upon the earth in which there is life I am giving
        every green plant as food.\u201D And it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And God saw everything that he had made and, behold, it was very
        good. And there was evening, and there was morning, a sixth day. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' And heaven and earth and all their array were finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And on the seventh day God finished his work that he had done, and
        he rested on the seventh day from all his work that he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Generations of Heaven and Earth'
      title: The Generations of Heaven and Earth
      number: 3
      content: 'And God blessed the seventh day, and he sanctified it, because on
        it he rested from all his work of creating that there was to do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "These are the generations of heaven and earth when they were created,
        in the day that Yahweh God made earth and heaven\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'before any plant of the field was on earth, and before any plant
        of the field had sprung up, because Yahweh God had not caused it to rain
        upon the earth, and there was no human being to cultivate the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "but a stream would rise from the earth and water the whole face of
        the ground\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'when Yahweh God formed the man of dust from the ground, and he blew
        into his nostrils the breath of life, and the man became a living creature. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Yahweh God planted a garden in Eden in the east, and there he
        put the man whom he had formed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Yahweh God caused to grow every tree that was pleasing to the
        sight and good for food. And the tree of life was in the midst of the garden,
        along with the tree of the knowledge of good and evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now a river flowed out from Eden that watered the garden, and from
        there it diverged and became four branches. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The name of the first is the Pishon. It went around all the land
        of Havilah, where there is gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '(The gold of that land is good; bdellium and onyx stones are there.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the name of the second is Gihon. It went around all the land
        of Cush. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the name of the third is Tigris. It flows east of Assyria. And
        the fourth river is the Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Yahweh God took the man and set him in the garden of Eden to
        cultivate it and to keep it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Yahweh God commanded the man, saying, \u201CFrom every tree of
        the garden you may freely eat,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "but from the tree of the knowledge of good and evil you shall not
        eat, for in the day that you eat from it you shall surely die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Yahweh God said, \u201Cit is not good that the man is alone.
        I will make for him a helper as his counterpart.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And out of the ground Yahweh God formed every beast of the field
        and every bird of the sky, and he brought each to the man to see what he
        would call it. And whatever the man called that living creature was its name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the man gave names to every domesticated animal and to the birds
        of heaven and to all the wild animals. But for the man there was not found
        a helper as his counterpart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Yahweh God caused a deep sleep to fall upon the man. While he
        slept, he took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh where it had been.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Yahweh God fashioned the rib which he had taken from the man
        into a woman and brought her to the man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the man said, \u201CShe is now bone from my bones and flesh from
        my flesh; she shall be called \u2018Woman,\u2019 for she was taken from man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Therefore a man shall leave his father and his mother and shall cling
        to his wife, and they shall be as one flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the man and his wife, both of them, were naked, and they were
        not ashamed. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall'
      title: The Fall
      number: 1
      content: "Now the serpent was more crafty than any other wild animal which
        Yahweh God had made. He said to the woman, \u201CDid God indeed say, \u2018You
        shall not eat from any tree in the garden\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The woman said to the serpent, \u201CFrom the fruit of the trees
        of the garden we may eat, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "but from the tree that is in the midst of the garden, God said, \u2018You
        shall not eat from it, nor shall you touch it, lest you die\u2019.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the serpent said to the woman, \u201CYou shall not surely die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For God knows that on the day you both eat from it, then your eyes
        will be opened and you both shall be like gods, knowing good and evil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the woman saw that the tree was good for food and that it was
        a delight to the eyes, and the tree was desirable to make one wise, then
        she took from its fruit and she ate. And she gave it also to her husband
        with her, and he ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the eyes of both of them were opened, and they knew that they
        were naked. And they sewed together fig leaves and they made for themselves
        coverings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then they heard the sound of Yahweh God walking in the garden at
        the windy time of day. And the man and his wife hid themselves from the presence
        of Yahweh God among the trees of the garden. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Yahweh God called to the man and said to him, \u201CWhere are
        you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he replied, \u201CI heard the sound of you in the garden, and
        I was afraid because I am naked, so I hid myself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then he asked, \u201CWho told you that you were naked? Have you eaten
        from the tree from which I forbade you to eat?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the man replied, \u201CThe woman whom you gave to be with me\u2014she
        gave to me from the tree and I ate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Yahweh God said to the woman, \u201CWhat is this you have done?\u201D
        And the woman said, \u201CThe serpent deceived me, and I ate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Yahweh God said to the serpent, \u201CBecause you have done
        this, you will be cursed more than any domesticated animal and more than
        any wild animal.  On your belly you shall go and dust you shall eat all the
        days of your life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I will put hostility between you and between the woman, and between
        your offspring and between her offspring;  he will strike you on the head,
        and you will strike him on the heel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "To the woman he said, \u201CI will greatly increase your pain in
        childbearing;  in pain you shall bear children. And to your husband shall
        be your desire. And he shall rule over you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And to Adam he said, \u201CBecause you listened to the voice of your
        wife and you ate from the tree from which I forbade you to eat,  the ground
        shall be cursed on your account. In pain you shall eat from it all the days
        of your life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And thorns and thistles shall sprout for you, and you shall eat the
        plants of the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "By the sweat of your brow  you shall eat bread, until your return
        to the ground. For from it you were taken; for you are dust, and to dust
        you shall return.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the man named his wife Eve, because she was the mother of all
        life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Yahweh God made for Adam and for his wife garments of skin, and
        he clothed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Yahweh God said, \u201CLook\u2014the man has become as one of
        us, to know good and evil. What if he stretches out his hand and takes also
        from the tree of life and eats, and lives forever?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Yahweh God sent him out from the garden of Eden, to till the
        ground from which he was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So he drove the man out, and placed cherubim east of the garden of
        Eden, and a flaming, turning sword to guard the way to the tree of life. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cain and Abel'
      title: Cain and Abel
      number: 1
      content: "Now Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bore Cain. And
        she said, \u201CI have given birth to a man with the help of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then she bore his brother Abel. And Abel became a keeper of sheep,
        and Cain became a tiller of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And in the course of time Cain brought an offering from the fruit
        of the ground to Yahweh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Abel also brought an offering from the choicest firstlings of
        his flock. And Yahweh looked with favor to Abel and to his offering, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'but to Cain and to his offering he did not look with favor. And Cain
        became very angry, and his face fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Yahweh said to Cain, \u201CWhy are you angry, and why is your
        face fallen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If you do well will I not accept you? But if you do not do well,
        sin is crouching at the door. And its desire is for you, but you must rule
        over it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Cain said to his brother Abel, \u201CLet us go out into the
        field.\u201D And when they were in the field, Cain rose up against his brother
        Abel and killed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Cain, \u201CWhere is Abel your brother?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CI do not know; am I my brother\u2019s keeper?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat have you done? The voice of your brother\u2019s
        blood is crying out to me from the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So now you are cursed from the ground, which has opened its mouth
        to receive the blood of your brother from your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When you till the ground it shall no longer yield its strength to
        you. You shall be a wanderer and a fugitive on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Cain said to Yahweh, \u201CMy punishment is greater than I can
        bear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Look, you have driven me out today from the face of the ground, and
        from your face I must hide. I will be a wanderer and a fugitive on the earth,
        and it will happen that whoever finds me will kill me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Yahweh said to him, \u201CTherefore, whoever kills Cain will
        be avenged sevenfold.\u201D Then Yahweh put a sign on Cain so that whoever
        found him would not kill him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Cain went out from the presence of Yahweh, and he settled in
        the land of Nod, east of Eden. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and gave birth to Enoch.
        And when he built a city he named the city after his son, Enoch.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And to Enoch was born Irad, and Irad fathered Mehujael, and Mehujael
        fathered Methushael, and Methushael fathered Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Lamech took to himself two wives. The name of the first was Adah,
        and the name of the second was Zillah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Adah gave birth to Jabal; he was the father of those who live
        in tents and those who have livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the name of his brother was Jubal; he was the father of all who
        play stringed instruments and wind instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Zillah also gave birth to Tubal-Cain who forged all kinds of
        tools of bronze and iron. And the sister of Tubal-Cain was Naamah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Lamech said to his wives, \u201CAdah and Zillah, listen to my
        voice; O wives of Lamech, hear my words. I have killed a man for wounding
        me, Even a young man for injuring me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'If Cain is avenged sevenfold, Then Lamech will be avenged seventy
        and seven times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Adam knew his wife again, and she gave birth to a son. And she
        called his name Seth, for she said \u201CGod has appointed to me another
        child in the place of Abel, because Cain killed him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And as for Seth, he also fathered a son, and he called his name Enosh.
        At that time he began to call on the name of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Adam\u2019s Descendants to Noah"
      title: "Adam\u2019s Descendants to Noah"
      number: 1
      content: 'This is the record of the generations of Adam. When God created Adam,
        he made him in the likeness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Male and female he created them. And he blessed them. And he called
        their name \u201CHumankind\u201D when they were created. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when Adam had lived one hundred and thirty years, he fathered
        a child in his likeness, according to his image. And he called his name Seth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the days of Adam after he fathered Seth were eight hundred years.
        And he fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And all the days of Adam which he lived were nine hundred and thirty
        years, and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Seth had lived one hundred and five years, he fathered Enosh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And after Seth had fathered Enosh he lived eight hundred and seven
        years, and fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And all the days of Seth were nine hundred and twelve years, and
        he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Enosh lived ninety years, he fathered Kenan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And after Enosh fathered Kenan he lived eight hundred and fifteen
        years, and fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And all the days of Enosh were nine hundred and five years, and he
        died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Kenan had lived seventy years, he fathered Mahalalel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And after Kenan had fathered Mahalalel, he lived eight hundred and
        forty years, and fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And all the days of Kenan were nine hundred and ten years, and he
        died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Mahalalel had lived sixty-five years, he fathered Jared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And after Mahalalel had fathered Jared, he lived eight hundred and
        thirty years, and fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And all the days of Mahalalel were eight hundred and ninety-five
        years, and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Jared had lived one hundred and sixty-two years, he fathered
        Enoch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And after Jared had fathered Enoch, he lived eight hundred years,
        and fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And all the days of Jared were nine hundred and sixty-two years,
        and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Enoch had lived sixty-five years, he fathered Methuselah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Enoch walked with God after he fathered Methuselah three hundred
        years, and fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And all the days of Enoch were three hundred and sixty-five years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Enoch walked with God, and he was no more, for God took him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Methuselah had lived one hundred and eighty-seven years, he
        fathered Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And after Methuselah had fathered Lamech, he lived seven hundred
        and eighty-two years, and fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And all the days of Methuselah were nine hundred and sixty-nine years,
        and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Lamech had lived one hundred and eighty-two years, he fathered
        a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And he called his name Noah, saying, \u201CThis one shall relieve
        us from our work, and from the hard labor of our hands, from the ground which
        Yahweh had cursed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And after Lamech had fathered Noah he lived five hundred and ninety-five
        years, and he fathered sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'All the days of Lamech were seven hundred and seventy-seven years,
        and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When Noah was five hundred years old, Noah fathered Shem, Ham, and
        Japheth. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prelude to the Flood'
      title: Prelude to the Flood
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that, when humankind began to multiply on the face
        of the ground, daughters were born to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the sons of God saw the daughters of humankind, that they were
        beautiful. And they took for themselves wives from all that they chose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Yahweh said, \u201CMy Spirit shall not abide with humankind forever
        in that he is also flesh. And his days shall be one hundred and twenty years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Nephilim were upon the earth in those days, and also afterward,
        when the sons of God went into the daughters of humankind, and they bore
        children to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Yahweh saw that the evil of humankind was great upon the earth,
        and every inclination of the thoughts of his heart was always only evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Yahweh regretted that he had made humankind on the earth, and
        he was grieved in his heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Yahweh said, \u201CI will destroy humankind whom I created from
        upon the face of the earth, from humankind, to animals, to creeping things,
        and to the birds of heaven, for I regret that I have made them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But Noah found favor in the eyes of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These are the generations of Noah. Noah was a righteous man, without
        defect in his generations. Noah walked with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Noah fathered three sons: Shem, Ham, and Japheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the earth was corrupted before God, and the earth was filled
        with violence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And God saw the earth, and behold, it was corrupt, for all flesh
        had corrupted its way upon the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And God said to Noah, \u201CThe end of all flesh has come before
        me, for the earth was filled with violence because of them. Now, look, I
        am going to destroy them along with the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Make for yourself an ark of cypress wood; you must make the ark with
        rooms, then you must cover it with pitch, inside and outside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And this is how you must make it: the length of the ark, three hundred
        cubits; its width fifty cubits; its height, thirty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You must make a roof for the ark, and finish it to a cubit above.
        And as for the door of the ark, you must put it in its side. You must make
        it with a lower, second, and a third deck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I, behold, I am about to bring the flood waters over the earth
        to destroy all flesh in which is the breath of life from under the heaven;
        everything that is on the earth shall perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I will establish my covenant with you, and you must go into the
        ark\u2014you, and your sons, and your wife, and the wives of your sons with
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And of every living thing, from all flesh, you must bring two from
        every kind into the ark to keep them alive with you; they shall be male and
        female. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "From the birds according to their kind, and from the animals according
        to their kind, from every creeping thing on the ground according to its kind\u2014two
        from every kind shall come to you to keep them alive. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And as for you, take for yourself from every kind of food that is
        eaten. And you must gather it to yourself. And it shall be for you and for
        them for food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Noah did according to all that God commanded him; thus he did. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " Then Yahweh said to Noah, \u201CGo\u2014you and all your household\u2014into
        the ark, for I have seen you are righteous before me in this generation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'From all the clean animals you must take for yourself seven pairs,
        a male and its mate. And from the animals that are not clean you must take
        two, a male and its mate, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'as well as from the birds of heaven seven pairs, male and female,
        to keep their kind alive on the face of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For within seven days I will send rain upon the earth for forty days
        and forty nights. And I will blot out all the living creatures that I have
        made from upon the face of the ground.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Flood'
      title: The Flood
      number: 5
      content: 'And Noah did according to all that Yahweh commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Noah was six hundred years old when the flood waters came upon the
        earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Noah and his sons and his wife, and the wives of his sons with
        him, went into the ark because of the waters of the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Of clean animals, and of animals which are not clean, and of the
        birds, and everything that creeps upon the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'two of each went to Noah, into the ark, male and female, as God had
        commanded Noah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And it happened that after seven days the waters of the flood came
        over the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "In the six hundredth year of the life of Noah, in the second month,
        on the seventeenth day of the month\u2014on that day all the springs of the
        great deep were split open, and the windows of heaven were opened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the rain came upon the earth forty days and forty nights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'On this same day, Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth, the sons of Noah,
        and the wife of Noah and the three wives of his sons with them, went into
        the ark, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'they and all the living creatures according to their kind, and all
        the domesticated animals according to their kind, and all the creatures that
        creep upon the earth according to their kind, all the birds according to
        their kind, every winged creature. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they came to Noah to the ark, two of each, from every living
        thing in which was the breath of life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And those that came, male and female, of every living thing, came
        as God had commanded him. And Yahweh shut the door behind him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the flood came forty days and forty nights upon the earth. And
        the waters increased, and lifted the ark, and it rose up from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the waters prevailed and increased greatly upon the earth. And
        the ark went upon the surface of the waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the waters prevailed overwhelmingly upon the earth, and they
        covered all the high mountains which were under the entire heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The waters swelled fifteen cubits above the mountains, covering them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And every living thing that moved on the earth perished\u2014the
        birds, and the domesticated animals, and the wild animals, and everything
        that swarmed on the earth, and all humankind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Everything in whose nostrils was the breath of life, among all that
        was on dry land, died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he blotted out every living thing upon the surface of the ground,
        from humankind, to animals, to creeping things, and to the birds of heaven;
        they were blotted out from the earth. Only Noah and those who were with him
        in the ark remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the waters prevailed over the earth one hundred and fifty days. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Flood Subsides'
      title: The Flood Subsides
      number: 1
      content: 'And God remembered Noah and all the wild animals, and all the domesticated
        animals that were with him in the ark. And God caused a wind to blow over
        the earth, and the waters subsided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the fountains of the deep and the windows of the heavens were
        closed, and the rain from the heavens was restrained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the waters receded from the earth gradually, and the waters abated
        at the end of one hundred and fifty days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the ark came to rest in the seventh month, on the seventeenth
        day of the month, on the mountains of Ararat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the waters continued to recede to the tenth month; in the tenth
        month, on the first of the month, the tops of the mountains appeared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And it happened that at the end of forty days Noah opened the window
        of the ark that he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he sent out a raven; it went to and fro until the waters were
        dried up from upon the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he sent out a dove to see whether the waters had subsided from
        upon the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But the dove did not find a resting place for the sole of her foot,
        and she returned to him into the ark, for the waters were still on the face
        of the earth. And he stretched out his hand and took her, and brought her
        to himself into the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he waited another seven days, and again he sent out the dove
        from the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the dove came to him in the evening, and behold, a freshly-picked
        olive tree leaf was in her mouth. And Noah knew that the waters had subsided
        from upon the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he waited seven more days, and he sent out the dove. But it did
        not return again to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it happened that, in the six hundred and first year, in the first
        month, on the first day of the month, the waters dried up from upon the earth.
        And Noah removed the covering of the ark and looked. And behold, the face
        of the ground was dried up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And in the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month,
        the earth was dry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And God spoke to Noah, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo out from the ark, you and your wife, and your sons, and
        your sons\u2019 wives with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Bring out with you all the living things which are with you, from
        all the living creatures\u2014birds, and animals, and everything that creeps
        on the earth, and let them swarm on the earth and be fruitful and multiply
        on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Noah went out, with his sons and his wife, and the wives of his
        sons with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Every animal, every creeping thing, and every bird, and everything
        that moves upon the earth, according to its families, went out from the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Noah built an altar to Yahweh, and he took from all the clean
        animals and from all the clean birds, and offered burnt offerings on the
        altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Yahweh smelled the soothing fragrance, and Yahweh said to himself,
        \u201CNever again will I curse the ground for the sake of humankind, because
        the inclination of the heart of humankind is evil from his youth. Nor will
        I ever again destroy all life as I have done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'As long as the earth endures, seed and harvest, cold and heat, summer
        and winter, day and night will not cease. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Covenant with Noah and Humankind"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with Noah and Humankind"
      number: 1
      content: "And God blessed Noah and his sons, and said to them, \u201CBe fruitful
        and multiply, and fill the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And fear of you and dread of you shall be upon every animal of the
        earth, and on every bird of heaven, and on everything that moves upon the
        ground, and on all the fish of the sea. Into your hand they shall be given. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every moving thing that lives shall be for you as food. As I gave
        the green plants to you, I have now given you everything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Only you shall not eat raw flesh with blood in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And your lifeblood I will require; from every animal I will require
        it. And from the hand of humankind, from the hand of each man to his brother
        I will require the life of humankind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAs for the one shedding the blood of humankind, by humankind
        his blood shall be shed, for God made humankind in his own image. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAnd you, be fruitful and multiply, swarm on the earth and multiply
        in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And God said to Noah and to his sons with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAs for me, behold, I am establishing my covenant with you and
        with your seed after you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and with every living creature that is with you\u2014the birds, the
        animals, and every animal of the earth with you, from all that came out of
        the ark to all the animals of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I am establishing my covenant with you, that never again will all
        flesh be cut off by the waters of a flood, nor will there ever be a flood
        that destroys the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And God said, \u201CThis is the sign of the covenant that I am making
        between me and you, and between every living creature that is with you for
        future generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'My bow I have set in the clouds, and it shall be for a sign of the
        covenant between me and between the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when I make clouds appear over the earth the bow shall be seen
        in the clouds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then I will remember my covenant that is between me and you, and
        between every living creature, with all flesh. And the waters of a flood
        will never again cause the destruction of all flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The bow shall be in the clouds, and I will see it, so as to remember
        the everlasting covenant between God and between every living creature, with
        all flesh that is upon the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Noah\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Noah\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 17
      content: "And God said to Noah, \u201CThis is the sign of the covenant which
        I am establishing between me and all flesh that is upon the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the sons of Noah who came out of the ark were Shem, Ham, and
        Japheth. (Ham was the father of Canaan.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These three were the sons of Noah, and from these the whole earth
        was populated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Noah began to be a man of the ground, and he planted a vineyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And he drank some of the wine and became drunk, and he exposed himself
        in the midst of his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and
        he told his two brothers outside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Shem and Japheth took a garment, and the two of them put it
        on their shoulders and, walking backward, they covered the nakedness of their
        father. And their faces were turned backward, so that they did not see the
        nakedness of their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Noah awoke from his drunkenness, and he knew what his youngest
        son had done to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And he said, \u201CCursed be Canaan, a slave of slaves he shall be
        to his brothers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBlessed be Yahweh, the God of Shem, and let Canaan
        be a slave to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "May God make space for Japheth, and let him dwell in the tents of
        Shem, and let Canaan be a slave for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Noah lived three hundred and fifty years after the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years, and he
        died. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Descendants of the Sons of Noah'
      title: The Descendants of the Sons of Noah
      number: 1
      content: "These are the generations of the sons of Noah\u2014Shem, Ham, and
        Japheth. Children were born to them after the flood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech,
        and Tiras. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'From these the coastland peoples spread out through their lands,
        each according to his own language by their own families, in their nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put, and Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca.
        The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Cush fathered Nimrod. He was the first on earth to be a mighty
        warrior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He was a mighty hunter before Yahweh. Therefore it was said, \u201CLike
        Nimrod a mighty hunter before Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now, the beginning of his kingdom was Babel, Erech, Akkad, and Calneh,
        in the land of Shinar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From that land he went out to Assyria, and he built Nineveh, Rehoboth-Ir,
        Calah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Resen between Nineveh and Calah; that is the great city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Egypt fathered Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Pathrusim, and Casluhim (from whom the Philistines came), and Caphtorim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Canaan fathered Sidon, his firstborn, and Heth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. Afterward the families
        of the Canaanites were spread abroad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the territory of the Canaanites was from Sidon in the direction
        of Gerar as far as Gaza, and in the direction of Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah,
        and Zeboiim, as far as Lasha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'These are the descendants of Ham, according to their families and
        their languages, in their lands, and in their nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And to Shem, the father of all the children of Eber, the older brother
        of Japheth, children were also born. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arphaxad, Lud, and Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Arphaxad fathered Shelah, and Shelah fathered Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And to Eber two sons were born. The name of the one was Peleg, for
        in his days the earth was divided, and the name of his brother was Joktan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Obal, Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And their dwelling place extended from Mesha in the direction of
        Sephar to the hill country of the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'These are the sons of Shem, according to their families, according
        to their languages, in their lands, and according to their nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'These are the families of the sons of Noah, according to their generations
        and in their nations. And from these the nations spread abroad on the earth
        after the flood. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tower of Babel'
      title: The Tower of Babel
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the whole earth had one language and the same words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And as people migrated from the east they found a plain in the land
        of Shinar and settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they said to each other, \u201CCome, let us make bricks and burn
        them thoroughly.\u201D And they had brick for stone and they had tar for
        mortar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they said, \u201CCome, let us build ourselves a city and a tower
        whose top reaches to the heavens. And let us make a name for ourselves, lest
        we be scattered over the face of the whole earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Yahweh came down to see the city and the tower that humankind
        was building. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Yahweh said, \u201CBehold, they are one people with one language,
        and this is only the beginning of what they will do. So now nothing that
        they intend to do will be impossible for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Come, let us go down and confuse their language there, so that they
        will not understand each other\u2019s language.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Yahweh scattered them from there over the face of the whole earth,
        and they stopped building the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Descendants of Shem'
      title: The Descendants of Shem
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore its name was called Babel, for there Yahweh confused the
        language of the whole earth, and there Yahweh scattered them over the face
        of the whole earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'These are the generations of Shem. When Shem was one hundred years
        old, he fathered Arphaxad, two years after the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Shem lived five hundred years after he fathered Arphaxad, and
        he fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Arphaxad had lived thirty-five years, he fathered Shelah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Arphaxad lived four hundred and three years after he fathered
        Shelah, and he fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Shelah had lived thirty years, he fathered Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Shelah lived four hundred and three years after he fathered Eber,
        and he fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Eber had lived thirty-four years, he fathered Peleg. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Eber lived four hundred and thirty years after he fathered Peleg,
        and he fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Peleg had lived thirty years, he fathered Reu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Peleg lived two hundred and nine years after he fathered Reu,
        and he fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Reu had lived thirty-two years, he fathered Serug. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Reu lived two hundred and seven years after he fathered Serug,
        and he fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When Serug had lived thirty years, he fathered Nahor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Serug lived two hundred years after he fathered Nahor, and he
        fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Nahor had lived twenty-nine years, he fathered Terah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Nahor lived one hundred and nineteen years after he fathered
        Terah, and he fathered other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: The Descendants of Terah'
      title: The Descendants of Terah
      number: 26
      content: 'When Terah had lived seventy years, he fathered Abram, Nahor, and
        Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now these are the generations of Terah. Terah fathered Abram, Nahor,
        and Haran, and Haran fathered Lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Haran died in the presence of Terah his father in the land of
        his birth, in Ur of the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Abram and Nahor took wives for themselves. The name of the wife
        of Abram was Sarai, and the name of the wife of Nahor was Milcah, the daughter
        of Haran, the father of Milcah and Iscah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Sarai was barren; she had no child. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Terah took Abram his son, and Lot, the son of Haran, his grandson,
        and Sarai his daughter-in-law, the wife of Abram his son, and went out with
        them from Ur of the Chaldeans to go to the land of Canaan. And they went
        to Haran, and they settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the days of Terah were two hundred and five years, and Terah
        died in Haran. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Call of Abram'
      title: The Call of Abram
      number: 1
      content: "And Yahweh said to Abram, \u201CGo out from your land and from your
        relatives, and from the house of your father, to the land that I will show
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I will make you a great nation, and I will bless you, and I will
        make your name great. And you will be a blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: "3: Abram\u2019s Journey"
      title: "Abram\u2019s Journey"
      number: 3
      content: "And I will bless those who bless you, and those who curse you I will
        curse. And all families of the earth will be blessed in you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Abram went out as Yahweh had told him, and Lot went with him.
        Now Abram was seventy-five years old when he went out from Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Abram took Sarai his wife, and Lot his nephew, and all their
        possessions that they had gathered, and all the persons that they had acquired
        in Haran, and they went out to go to the land of Canaan. And they went to
        the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Abram traveled through the land up to the place of Shechem, to
        the Oak of Moreh. Now the Canaanites were in the land at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Yahweh appeared to Abram and said, \u201CTo your offspring I
        will give this land.\u201D And he built an altar there to Yahweh, who had
        appeared to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he moved on from there to the hill country, east of Bethel. And
        he pitched his tent at Bethel on the west, and at Ai on the east. And he
        built an altar there to Yahweh. And he called on the name of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Abram kept moving on, toward the Negev. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And there was a famine in the land. And Abram went down to Egypt
        to dwell as an alien there, for the famine was severe in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And it happened that as he drew near to enter into Egypt, he said
        to Sarai his wife, \u201CLook now, I know that you are a woman beautiful
        of appearance, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and it shall happen that, if the Egyptians see you, then they will
        say, \u2018This is his wife,\u2019 then they will kill me but let you live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Please say you are my sister so that it will go well for me on your
        account. Then I will live on account of you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And it happened that as Abram came into Egypt, the Egyptians saw
        the woman, that she was very beautiful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the officials of Pharaoh saw her, and they praised her beauty
        to Pharaoh. And the woman was taken to the house of Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he dealt well with Abram on account of her, and he had sheep,
        cattle, male donkeys, male servants, female servants, female donkeys, and
        camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Yahweh afflicted Pharaoh and his household with severe plagues
        on account of the matter of Sarai the wife of Abram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Pharaoh called for Abram and said, \u201CWhat is this you have
        done to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why did you say \u2018She is my sister,\u2019 so that I took her
        to myself as a wife? Now then, here is your wife. Take her and go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Pharaoh commanded his men concerning him, and then sent him and
        his wife and all that was with him away. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Parting of Abram and Lot'
      title: The Parting of Abram and Lot
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Abram went up from Egypt, he and his wife and all that was with
        him. And Lot went with him to the Negev. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now Abram was very wealthy in livestock, in silver, and in gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he went according to his journey from the Negev, then to Bethel,
        to the place where his tent was at the beginning, between Bethel and Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'to the place where he had made an altar at the beginning. And Abram
        called on the name of Yahweh there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Lot, who went with Abram, also had herds and tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the land could not support them so as to live together, because
        their possessions were so many that they were not able to live together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And there was a quarrel between the herdsmen of the livestock of
        Abram and the herdsmen of the livestock of Lot. Now at that time the Canaanites
        and the Perizzites were living in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abram said to Lot, \u201CPlease, let there not be quarreling
        between me and you, and between my shepherds and your shepherds, for we men
        are brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Is not the whole land before you? Separate yourself from me. If you
        want what is on the left, then I will go right; if you want what is on the
        right, I will go left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Lot lifted up his eyes and saw the whole plain of the Jordan,
        that all of it was well-watered land\u2014this was before Yahweh destroyed
        Sodom and Gomorrah\u2014like the garden of Yahweh, like the land of Egypt
        in the direction of Zoar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Lot chose for himself all the plain of the Jordan. And Lot journeyed
        from the east, and so they separated from each other.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abram settled in the land of Canaan, and Lot settled in the cities
        of the plain. And he pitched his tent toward Sodom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the men of Sodom were extremely wicked sinners against Yahweh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Yahweh said to Abram after Lot had separated from him, \u201CNow,
        lift up your eyes and look from the place where you are to the north, and
        to the south, and to the east and to the west, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'for all the land which you see I will give to you, and to your descendants,
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I will make your descendants like the dust of the earth which, if
        anyone were able to count the dust of the earth, your descendants would be
        so counted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Arise, go through the length of the land and through its breadth,
        for I will give it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Abram pitched his tent, and he came and settled at the oaks of
        Mamre, which were at Hebron. And there he built an altar to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram Rescues Lot'
      title: Abram Rescues Lot
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that in the days of Amraphel, the king of Shinar,
        Arioch, the king of Ellasar, Kedorlaomer, the king of Elam, and Tidal, the
        king of Goiim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'made war with Bera, the king of Sodom, and Birsha, the king of Gomorrah,
        Shinab, the king of Admah, and Shemeber, the king of Zeboiim, and the king
        of Bela (that is, Zoar). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All these joined forces at the valley of Siddim (that is, the sea
        of the salt). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Twelve years they had served Kedorlaomer, but in the thirteenth year
        they rebelled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the fourteenth year Kedorlaomer and the kings who were with him
        came and defeated the Rephaim in Ashteroth-Karnaim, and the Zuzim in Ham,
        and the Emim in Shaveh-Kiriathaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Horites in their hill country of Seir, as far as El-Paran,
        which is at the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then they turned back and came to En-Mishpat (that is, Kadesh). And
        they defeated the whole territory of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites
        who were living in Hazazon-Tamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the king of Sodom, the king of Gomorrah, the king of Admah,
        the king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar) went out, and they
        took up battle position in the Valley of Siddim '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'with Kedorlaomer, king of Elam, and Tidal, king of Goiim, and Amraphel,
        king of Shinar, and Arioch, king of Ellasar, four kings against five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the Valley of Siddim was full of tar pits. And the kings of Sodom
        and Gomorrah fled and fell into them, but the rest fled to the mountains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So they took all the possessions of Sodom and Gomorrah and all their
        provisions, and they left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they took Lot, the son of the brother of Abram, and his possessions,
        and left. (Now he had been living in Sodom.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then one who escaped came and told Abram the Hebrew. And he was living
        at the oaks of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol and brother of Aner.
        They were allies with Abram.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Abram heard that his relative was taken captive, he summoned
        his trained men, born in his house, three hundred and eighteen of them, and
        he went in pursuit up to Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he divided his trained men against them at night, he and his
        servants. And he defeated them and pursued them to Hobah, which is north
        of Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Abram Meets Melchizedek'
      title: Abram Meets Melchizedek
      number: 16
      content: 'And he brought back all the possessions. And he also brought back
        Lot, his relative, and his possessions, and the women and the people as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'After his return from defeating Kedorlaomer and the kings who were
        with him, the king of Sodom went out to meet him at the Valley of Shaveh
        (that is, the Valley of the King). '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Melchizedek, the king of Salem, brought out bread and wine. (He
        was the priest of God Most High). '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he blessed him and said, \u201CBlessed be Abram by God Most High,
        Maker of heaven and earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And blessed be God Most High who delivered your enemies into your
        hand.\u201D And he gave to him a tenth of everything. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the king of Sodom said to Abram, \u201CGive me the people, but
        the possessions take for yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Abram said to the king of Sodom, \u201CI have raised my hand
        to Yahweh, God Most High, Maker of heaven and earth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "that neither a thread nor a thong of a sandal would I take from all
        that belongs to you, that you might not say, \u2018I made Abram rich.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Nothing besides what the servants have eaten and the share of the
        men who went out with me will I take. Let Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre take their
        share.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Covenant with Abram"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Covenant with Abram"
      number: 1
      content: "After these things the word of Yahweh came to Abram in a vision,
        saying: \u201CDo not be afraid, Abram; I am your shield, and your reward
        shall be very great.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Abram said, \u201CO Yahweh, my Lord, what will you give me?
        I continue to be childless, and my heir is Eliezer of Damascus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Abram said, \u201CLook, you have not given me a descendant, and
        here, a member of my household is my heir.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And behold, the word of Yahweh came to him saying, \u201CThis person
        will not be your heir, but your own son will be your heir.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he brought him outside and said, \u201CLook toward the heavens
        and count the stars if you are able to count them.\u201D And he said to him,
        \u201CSo shall your offspring be.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he believed in Yahweh, and he reckoned it to him as righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CI am Yahweh, who brought you out from Ur
        of the Chaldeans to give this land to you, to possess it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said, \u201CO Yahweh God, how shall I know that I will possess
        it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CTake for me a three-year-old heifer, and
        a three-year-old female goat, and a three-year-old ram, and a turtledove
        and a young pigeon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he took for him all these and cut them in pieces down the middle.
        And he put each piece opposite the other, but the birds he did not cut. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the birds of prey came down on the carcasses, but Abram drove
        them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And it happened that, as the sun went down, then a deep sleep fell
        upon Abram and, behold, a great terrifying darkness fell upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said to Abram, \u201CYou must surely know that your descendants
        shall be as aliens in a land not their own. And they shall serve them and
        they shall oppress them four hundred years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And also that the nation which they serve I will judge. Then afterward
        they shall go out with great possessions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And as for you, you shall go to your ancestors in peace; you shall
        be buried in a good old age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the fourth generation shall return here, for the guilt of the
        Amorites is not yet complete.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And after the sun had gone down and it was dusk, behold, a smoking
        firepot and a flaming torch passed between those half pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On that day Yahweh made a covenant with Abram saying, \u201CTo your
        offspring I will give this land, from the river of Egypt to the great river,
        the Euphrates river, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the land of the Kenites, the Kenizzites, the Kadmonites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sarai and Hagar'
      title: Sarai and Hagar
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Sarai, the wife of Abram, had borne him no children. And she
        had a female Egyptian servant, and her name was Hagar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Sarai said to Abram, \u201CLook, please, Yahweh has prevented
        me from bearing children. Please go in to my servant; perhaps I will have
        children by her.\u201D And Abram listened to the voice of Sarai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Sarai, the wife of Abram, took Hagar, her Egyptian servant,
        after Abram had lived ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to Abram
        her husband as his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he went in to Hagar, and she conceived. And when she saw that
        she had conceived, then her mistress grew small in her eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Sarai said to Abram, \u201Cmay my harm be upon you. I had my
        servant sleep with you, and when she saw that she had conceived, she no longer
        respected me. May Yahweh judge between me and you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Hagar and the Angel of Yahweh'
      title: Hagar and the Angel of Yahweh
      number: 6
      content: "And Abram said to Sarai, \u201CLook, your servant is under your authority.
        Do to her that which is good in your eyes.\u201D And Sarai mistreated her,
        and she fled from her presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the angel of Yahweh found her at a spring of water in the wilderness,
        at the spring by the road of Shur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said to Hagar, the servant of Sarai, \u201CFrom where have
        you come, and where are you going?\u201D And she said, \u201CI am fleeing
        from the presence of Sarai my mistress.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the angel of Yahweh said to her, \u201CReturn to your mistress
        and submit yourself under her authority.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the angel of Yahweh said to her, \u201CI will greatly multiply
        your offspring, so that they cannot be counted for their abundance.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the angel of Yahweh said to her: \u201CBehold, you are pregnant
        and shall have a son. And you shall call his name Ishmael, for Yahweh has
        listened to your suffering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he shall be a wild donkey of a man, his hand will be against
        everyone, and the hand of everyone will be against him, and he will live
        in hostility with all his brothers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So she called the name of Yahweh who spoke to her, \u201CYou are
        El-Roi,\u201D for she said, \u201CHere I have seen after he who sees me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the well was called Beer-Lahai-Roi; behold, it is between
        Kadesh and Bered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Hagar had a child for Abram, a son. And Abram called the name
        of his son whom Hagar bore to him, Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Abram was eighty-six years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to Abram. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram and Circumcision, the Sign of the Covenant'
      title: Abram and Circumcision, the Sign of the Covenant
      number: 1
      content: "When Abram was ninety-nine years old Yahweh appeared to Abram. And
        he said to him, \u201CI am El-Shaddai; walk before me and be blameless "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "so that I may make my covenant between me and you, and may multiply
        you exceedingly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Abram fell upon his face and God spoke with him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAs for me, behold, my covenant shall be with you, and you shall
        be the father of a multitude of nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your name shall no longer be called Abram, but your name shall be
        Abraham, for I will make you the father of a multitude of nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I will make you exceedingly fruitful. I will make you a nation,
        and kings shall go out from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will establish my covenant between me and you, and between
        your offspring after you, throughout their generations as an everlasting
        covenant to be as God for you and to your offspring after you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I will give to you and to your offspring after you the land in
        which you are living as an alien, all the land of Canaan, as an everlasting
        property. And I will be to them as God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And God said to Abraham, \u201CNow as for you, you must keep my covenant,
        you and your offspring after you, throughout their generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This is my covenant which you shall keep, between me and you, and
        also with your offspring after you: Every male among you shall be circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall circumcise the flesh of your foreskin, and it shall
        be a sign of the covenant between me and you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And at eight days of age you shall yourselves circumcise every male
        belonging to your generations and the servant born in your house and the
        one bought from any foreigner who is not from your offspring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You must certainly circumcise the servant born in your house and
        the one bought from any foreigner. And my covenant shall be with your flesh
        as an everlasting covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And as for any uncircumcised male who has not circumcised the flesh
        of his foreskin, that person shall be cut off from his people. He has broken
        my covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And God said to Abraham, \u201Cas for Sarai your wife, you shall
        not call her name Sarai, for Sarah shall be her name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I will bless her; moreover, I give to you from her a son. And
        I will bless her, and she shall give rise to nations. Kings of peoples shall
        come from her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Abraham fell upon his face and laughed. And he said in his heart,
        \u201CCan a child be born to a man a hundred years old, or can Sarah bear
        a child at ninety?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Abraham said to God, \u201COh that Ishmael might live before
        you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And God said, \u201CNo, but Sarah your wife shall bear a son for
        you, and you shall call his name Isaac. And I will establish my covenant
        with him as an everlasting covenant to his offspring after him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And as for Ishmael, I have heard you. Behold, I will bless him and
        I will make him fruitful, and I will multiply him exceedingly. He shall father
        twelve princes, and I will make him a great nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But my covenant I will establish with Isaac, whom Sarah shall bear
        to you at this appointed time next year.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When he finished speaking with him, God went up from Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Abraham took Ishmael his son and all who were born of his house,
        and all those acquired by his money, every male among the men of Abraham\u2019s
        house, and he circumcised the flesh of their foreskin on the same day that
        God spoke with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Abraham was ninety-nine years old when he circumcised the flesh of
        his foreskin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he circumcised the
        flesh of his foreskin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Abraham and his son Ishmael were circumcised on the same day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And all the men of his house, those born in the house, and those
        acquired by money from a foreigner, were circumcised with him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Appears to Abraham as a Man'
      title: Yahweh Appears to Abraham as a Man
      number: 1
      content: 'And Yahweh appeared to him by the oaks of Mamre. And he was sitting
        in the doorway of the tent at the heat of the day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he lifted up his eyes and saw, and behold, three men were standing
        near him. And he saw them and ran from the doorway of the tent to meet them.
        And he bowed down to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he said, \u201CMy lord, if I have found favor in your eyes do
        not pass by your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let a little water be brought and wash your feet, and rest under
        the tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And let me bring a piece of bread, then refresh yourselves. Afterward
        you can pass on, once you have passed by with your servant.\u201D Then they
        said, \u201CDo so as you have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Abraham hastened into the tent to Sarah, and he said, \u201CQuickly\u2014make
        three seahs of fine flour for kneading and make bread cakes!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Abraham ran to the cattle and took a calf, tender and good, and
        gave it to the servant, and he made haste to prepare it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he took curds and milk, and the calf which he prepared, and
        set it before them. And he was standing by them under the tree while they
        ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWhere is Sarah your wife?\u201D And he
        said, \u201CHere, in the tent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he said, \u201CI will certainly return to you in the spring,
        and look, Sarah your wife will have a son.\u201D Now Sarah was listening
        at the doorway of the tent, and which was behind him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Abraham and Sarah were old, advanced in age; the way of women
        had ceased to be for Sarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Sarah laughed to herself saying, \u201CAfter I am worn out and
        my husband is old, shall this pleasure be to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Abraham, \u201CWhat is this that Sarah laughed,
        saying, \u2018Is it indeed true that I will bear a child, now that I have
        grown old?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Is anything too difficult for Yahweh? At the appointed time I will
        return to you in the spring and Sarah shall have a son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Sarah denied it, saying, \u201CI did not laugh,\u201D because
        she was afraid. He said, \u201CNo, but you did laugh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the men set out from there, and they looked down upon Sodom.
        And Abraham went with them to send them on their way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Yahweh said, \u201CShall I conceal from Abraham what I am going
        to do? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Abraham will surely become a great and strong nation, and all the
        nations of the earth will be blessed on account of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For I have chosen him, that he will command his children and his
        household after him that they will keep the way of Yahweh, to do righteousness
        and justice, so that Yahweh may bring upon Abraham that which he said to
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Yahweh said, \u201CBecause the outcry of Sodom and Gomorrah
        is great and because their sin is very serious,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Abraham Intercedes for Sodom'
      title: Abraham Intercedes for Sodom
      number: 21
      content: "I will go down and I will see. Have they done altogether according
        to its cry of distress which has come to me? If not, I will know.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the men turned from there and went toward Sodom. And Abraham
        was still standing before Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Abraham drew near to Yahweh and said, \u201CWill you also sweep
        away the righteous with the wicked? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'If perhaps there are fifty righteous in the midst of the city, will
        you also sweep them away and not forgive the place on account of the fifty
        righteous in her midst? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Far be it from you to do such a thing as this, to kill the righteous
        with the wicked, that the righteous would be as the wicked! Far be it from
        you! Will not the Judge of all the earth do justice?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Yahweh said, \u201CIf I find fifty righteous in Sodom, in the
        midst of the city, then I will forgive the whole place for their sake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Abraham answered and said, \u201CLook, please, I was bold to
        speak to my Lord, but I am dust and ashes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Perhaps the fifty righteous are lacking five\u2014will you destroy
        the whole city on account of the five?\u201D And he answered, \u201CI will
        not destroy it if I find forty-five there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And once again he spoke to him and said, \u201CWhat if forty are
        found there?\u201D And he answered, \u201CI will not do it on account of
        the forty.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he said, \u201CPlease, let not my Lord be angry, and I will speak.
        What if thirty be found there?\u201D And he answered, \u201CI will not do
        it if I find thirty there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CPlease, now, I was bold to speak to my Lord. What
        if twenty be found there?\u201D And he answered, \u201CI will not destroy
        it for the sake of the twenty.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And he said, \u201CPlease, let not my Lord be angry, and I will speak
        only once more. What if ten are found there?\u201D And he answered, \u201CI
        will not destroy it for the sake of the ten.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Yahweh left, as he finished speaking to Abraham, and Abraham
        returned to his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rescue of Lot from Sodom'
      title: The Rescue of Lot from Sodom
      number: 1
      content: 'And the two angels came to Sodom in the evening. And Lot was sitting
        in the gateway of Sodom. Then Lot saw them and stood up to meet them. And
        he bowed down with his face to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CBehold, my lords, please turn aside into the house
        of your servant and spend the night and wash your feet. Then you can rise
        early and go on your way.\u201D And they said, \u201CNo, but we will spend
        the night in the square.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But he urged them strongly, and they turned aside with him and came
        into his house. And he made a meal for them and baked unleavened bread, and
        they ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Before they laid down, the men of the city, the men of Sodom, both
        young and old, all the people to the last man, surrounded the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And they called to Lot and said to him, \u201CWhere are the men who
        came to you tonight? Bring them out to us so that we may know them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But Lot went out to them at the entrance, and he shut the door behind
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said, \u201CNo, my brothers, please do not do such a wrong
        thing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Behold, I have two daughters who have not known a man. Please, let
        me bring them out to you; then do to them as it seems good in your eyes.
        Only to these men do not do this thing, since they came under my roof for
        protection.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But they said, \u201CStep aside!\u201D Then they said, \u201CThis
        fellow came to dwell as a foreigner and he acts as a judge! Now we shall
        do worse to you than them!\u201D And they pressed very hard against the man,
        against Lot, and they drew near to break the door. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the men reached out with their hands and brought Lot in to them,
        into the house, and they shut the door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the men who were at the entrance of the house they struck with
        blindness, both small and great, and they were unable to find the entrance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the men said to Lot, \u201CWho is here with you? Bring out from
        the place your sons-in-law, and your sons and your daughters, and all who
        are with you in the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For we are about to destroy this place, because their cry has become
        great before Yahweh. Yahweh sent us to destroy it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Lot went out and spoke to his sons-in-law who were taking his
        daughters and said, \u201CGet up! Go out from this place, because Yahweh
        is going to destroy the city!\u201D But it seemed like a joke in the eyes
        of his sons-in-law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And as the dawn came up the angels urged Lot saying, \u201CGet up,
        take your wife and your two daughters who are staying with you, lest you
        be destroyed with the punishment of the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But when he lingered, the men seized him by his hand and his wife\u2019s
        hand, and his two daughters by hand, on account of the mercy of Yahweh upon
        him. And they brought him out and set him outside of the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And after bringing them outside one said, \u201CFlee for your life;
        do not look behind you, and do not stand anywhere in the plain. Flee to the
        mountains lest you be destroyed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Lot said to them, \u201CNo, please, my lords. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, your servant has found favor in your eyes and you have shown
        me great kindness in saving my life. But I cannot flee to the mountains,
        lest the disaster overtake me and I die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Behold, this city is near enough to flee there, and it is a little
        one. Please, let me flee there. Is it not a little one? Then my life shall
        be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CBehold, I will grant this favor as well;
        that I will not overthrow the city of which you have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Destruction of Sodom'
      title: The Destruction of Sodom
      number: 22
      content: "Escape there quickly, for I cannot do this thing until you get there.\u201D
        Therefore, there name of the city was called Zoar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After the sun had risen upon the earth and Lot had entered Zoar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yahweh rained down from heaven upon Sodom and Gomorrah brimstone
        and fire from Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he overthrew those cities and the whole plain, and the inhabitants
        of the cities and the vegetation of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But his wife looked back, and she became a pillar of salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Abraham arose early in the morning and went to the place where
        he had stood before Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he looked down upon the surface of Sodom and Gomorrah, and upon
        the whole surface of the land, the plain. And he saw that, behold, the smoke
        of the land went up like the smoke of a smelting furnace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Lot and His Daughters'
      title: Lot and His Daughters
      number: 29
      content: 'So it was, when God destroyed the cities of the plain that God remembered
        Abraham and sent Lot out from the midst of the overthrow, when he overthrew
        the cities in which Lot lived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Lot went out from Zoar and settled in the hill country with his
        two daughters, for he was afraid to stay in Zoar. So he lived in a cave,
        he and his two daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And the firstborn daughter said to the younger one, \u201COur father
        is old, and there is no man in the land to come in to us according to the
        manner of all the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Come, let us give our father wine to drink and let us lie with him
        that we may secure descendants through our father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they gave their father wine to drink that night, and the firstborn
        went and lay with her father, but he did not know when she lay down or when
        she got up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And it happened that, the next day the firstborn said to the younger
        one, \u201CLook, I laid with my father last night. Let us give him wine to
        drink also tonight, then go and lie with him that we may secure descendants
        through our father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And they gave their father wine to drink again that night, and the
        younger got up and lay with him, but he did not know when she lay down or
        when she got up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And the two daughters of Lot became pregnant by their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The firstborn gave birth to a son, and she called his name Moab.
        He is the father of Moab until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the younger, she also gave birth to a son, and she called his
        name Ben-Ammi. He is the father of the Ammonites until this day. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abraham and Abimelech'
      title: Abraham and Abimelech
      number: 1
      content: 'And Abraham journeyed from there to the land of the Negev, and he
        settled between Kadesh and Shur. And he dwelled as an alien in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Abraham said about Sarah his wife, \u201CShe is my sister.\u201D
        And Abimelech king of Gerar sent and took Sarah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And God came to Abimelech in a dream at night. And he said to him,
        \u201CLook, you are a dead man on account of the woman you have taken. For
        she is a married woman.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now Abimelech had not approached her, so he said, \u201Cmy Lord,
        will you even kill a righteous people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Did not he himself say to me, \u2018She is my sister\u2019? And she
        herself said, \u2018He is my brother.\u2019 With integrity of my heart and
        with cleanness of my hands I did this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then God said to him in the dream, \u201CYes, I know that in the
        integrity of your heart you did this, and I also kept you from sinning against
        me. Therefore, I did not allow you to touch her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So now, return the wife of the man, for he is a prophet, so that
        he will pray for you and you will live. And if you do not return her, know
        that you will certainly die, and all that are yours.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Abimelech rose early in the morning. And he called all his servants
        and told them all these things, and the men were very afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Abimelech called for Abraham and said to him, \u201CWhat have
        you done to us? And how have I sinned against you that you brought upon me
        and upon my kingdom a great sin? You have done things to me that should not
        be done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Abimelech said to Abraham, \u201CWhat were you thinking that
        you did this thing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CBecause I thought, surely there is no fear
        of God in this place; they will kill me on account of the matter of my wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Besides, she is my sister, the daughter of my father, but not the
        daughter of my mother. And she became my wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it happened that as God caused me to wander from the house of
        my father I said to her, \u2018This is your loyal kindness that you must
        do for me at every place where we come: say concerning me, \u201CHe is my
        brother.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Abimelech took sheep and cattle and male slaves and female slaves,
        and he gave them to Abraham. And he returned Sarah his wife to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Abimelech said, \u201CHere is my land before you; settle where
        it pleases you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And to Sarah he said, \u201CLook, I have given a thousand pieces
        of silver to your brother. It shall be an exoneration. You are vindicated
        before all who are with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Abraham prayed to God, and God healed Abimelech and his wife
        and his female servants so that they could bear children again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For Yahweh had completely closed up all the wombs of the house of
        Abimelech because of the matter of Sarah, the wife of Abraham. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Birth of Isaac'
      title: The Birth of Isaac
      number: 1
      content: 'And Yahweh visited Sarah as he had said. And Yahweh did to Sarah
        as he had promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And she conceived, and Sarah bore to Abraham a son in his old age
        at the appointed time that God had told him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him, whom
        Sarah bore to him, Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Abraham circumcised Isaac his son when he was eight days old,
        as God had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Abraham was one hundred years old when Isaac his son was born
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Sarah said, \u201CGod has made laughter for me; all who hear
        will laugh for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Hagar and Ishmael'
      title: Hagar and Ishmael
      number: 7
      content: "And she said, \u201CWho would announce to Abraham that Sarah would
        nurse children? Yet I have borne a son to Abraham in his old age.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the child grew and was weaned. And Abraham made a great feast
        on the day Isaac was weaned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Sarah saw the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne Abraham,
        mocking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then she said to Abraham, \u201CDrive out this slave woman and her
        son, for the son of this slave woman will not be heir with my son, with Isaac.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the matter displeased Abraham very much on account of his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then God said to Abraham, \u201CDo not be displeased on account of
        the boy and on account of the slave woman. Listen to everything that Sarah
        said to you, for through Isaac your offspring will be named. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And I will also make the son of the slave woman into a nation, for
        he is your offspring.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Abraham rose up early in the morning and took bread and a skin
        of water and gave it to Hagar, putting it on her shoulder. And he sent her
        away with the child, and she went, wandering about in the wilderness, in
        Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And when the water was finished from the skin, she put the child
        under one of the bushes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And she went and she sat a good distance away, for she said, \u201CLet
        me not see the child\u2019s death.\u201D So she sat away from him and lifted
        up her voice and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And God heard the cry of the boy and the angel of God called to Hagar
        from the heavens and said to her, \u201CWhat is the matter Hagar? Do not
        be afraid, for God has heard the cry of the boy from where he is.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Get up, take up the boy and take him with your hand, for I will make
        him a great nation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And God opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water. And she went
        and filled the skin with water and gave a drink to the boy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And God was with the boy, and he grew and lived in the wilderness.
        And he became an expert with a bow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Covenant Between Abraham and Abimelech'
      title: The Covenant Between Abraham and Abimelech
      number: 21
      content: 'And he lived in the wilderness of Paran. And his mother took a wife
        for him from the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And it happened that at that time, Abimelech and Phicol, the commander
        of his army, said to Abraham, \u201CGod is with you, in all that you do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So now, swear to me here by God that you will not deal with me falsely,
        or with my descendants, or my posterity. According to the kindness that I
        have done to you, you shall pledge to do with me and with the land where
        you have dwelled as an alien.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CI swear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Abraham complained to Abimelech on account of the well of water
        that servants of Abimelech had seized. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Abimelech said, \u201CI do not know who did this thing, neither
        did you tell me, nor have I heard of it except for today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Abraham took sheep and cattle and gave them to Abimelech. And
        the two of them made a covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Abraham set off seven ewe-lambs of the flock by themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And Abimelech said to Abraham, \u201CWhat is the meaning of these
        seven ewe-lambs that you have set off by themselves?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he said, \u201CYou shall take the seven ewe-lambs from my hand
        as proof on my behalf that I dug this well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore that place is called Beersheba, because there the two of
        them swore an oath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And they made a covenant at Beersheba. And Abimelech, and Phicol
        his army commander stood and returned to the land of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he planted a tamarisk tree in Beersheba, and there he called
        on the name of Yahweh, the everlasting God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Abraham dwelled as an alien in the land of the Philistines many
        days. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Tests Abraham'
      title: God Tests Abraham
      number: 1
      content: "And it happened that after these things, God tested Abraham. And
        he said to him, \u201CAbraham!\u201D And he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CTake your son, your only child, Isaac, whom you
        love, and go to the land of Moriah, and offer him there as a burnt offering
        on one of the mountains where I will tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Abraham rose up early in the morning and saddled his donkey.
        And he took two of his servants with him, and Isaac his son. And he chopped
        wood for a burnt offering. And he got up and went to the place which God
        had told him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the third day Abraham lifted up his eyes, and he saw the place
        at a distance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Abraham said to his servants, \u201CYou stay here with the donkey,
        and I and the boy will go up there. We will worship, then we will return
        to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering and placed it on
        Isaac his son. And he took the fire in his hand and the knife, and the two
        of them went together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Isaac said to Abraham his father, \u201CMy father!\u201D And
        he said, \u201CHere I am, my son.\u201D And he said, \u201CHere is the fire
        and the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CGod will provide the lamb for a burnt offering,
        my son.\u201D And the two of them went together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they came to the place that God had told him. And Abraham built
        an altar there and arranged the wood. Then he bound Isaac his son and placed
        him on the altar atop the wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Abraham stretched out his hand and took the knife to slaughter
        his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the angel of Yahweh called to him from heaven and said, \u201CAbraham!
        Abraham!\u201D And he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u201CDo not stretch out your hand against the boy;
        do not do anything to him. For now I know that you are one who fears God,
        since you have not withheld your son, your only child, from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Abraham lifted up his eyes and looked. And behold, a ram was
        caught in the thicket by his horns. And Abraham went and took the ram, and
        offered it as a burnt offering in place of his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Abraham called the name of that place \u201CYahweh will provide,\u201D
        for which reason it is said today, \u201Con the mountain of Yahweh it shall
        be provided.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the angel of Yahweh called to Abraham a second time from heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CI swear by myself, declares Yahweh, that because
        you have done this thing and have not withheld your son, your only child, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'that I will certainly bless you and greatly multiply your offspring
        as the stars of heaven, and as the sand that is by the shore of the sea.
        And your offspring will take possession of the gate of his enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "All the nations of the earth will be blessed through your offspring,
        because you have listened to my voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Abraham returned to his servants, and they got up and went together
        to Beersheba. And Abraham lived in Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And it happened that after these things, it was told to Abraham,
        \u201CLook, Milcah has also borne children to your brother Nahor: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Uz his firstborn and Buz his brother, and Kemuel the father of Aram, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "and Kesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph, and Bethuel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '(Now, Bethuel fathered Rebekah). These eight Milcah bore to Nahor,
        the brother of Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And his concubine, whose name was Reumah, also bore Tebah, Gaham,
        Tahash, and Maacah. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Sarah\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Sarah\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 1
      content: 'And Sarah lived one hundred and twenty-seven years; these were the
        years of the life of Sarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Sarah died in Kiriath Arba; that is Hebron, in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Abraham went to mourn for Sarah and to weep for her. And Abraham
        rose up from his dead, and he spoke to the Hittites and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI am a stranger and an alien among you; give to me my own burial
        site among you so that I may bury my dead from before me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the Hittites answered Abraham and said to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CHear us, my lord, you are a mighty prince in our midst. Bury
        your dead in the choicest of our burial sites. None of us will withhold his
        burial site from you for burying your dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Abraham rose up and bowed to the people of the land, to the Hittites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he spoke with them, saying, \u201CIf you are willing that I bury
        my dead from before me, hear me and intercede for me with Ephron the son
        of Zohar, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "that he may sell to me the cave of Machpelah which belongs to him,
        which is at the end of his field. At full value let him sell it to me in
        your midst as a burial site.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Ephron was sitting among the Hittites. And Ephron the Hittite
        answered Abraham in the hearing of the Hittites with respect to all who were
        entering the gate of his city, and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNo, my lord, hear me. I give you the field and the cave which
        is in it, I also give it to you in the sight of the children of my people
        I give it to you. Bury your dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Abraham bowed before the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he spoke to Ephron in the hearing of the people of the land,
        saying, \u201CIf only you will hear me\u2014I give the price of the field.
        Take it from me that I may bury my dead there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Ephron answered Abraham, saying to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CMy lord, hear me. A piece of land worth four hundred shekels
        of silver\u2014what is that between me and you? Bury your dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Abraham listened to Ephron, and Abraham weighed for Ephron the
        silver that he had named in the hearing of the Hittites: four hundred shekels
        of silver at the merchants\u2019 current rate.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the field of Ephron which was in the Machpelah, which was near
        Mamre\u2014the field and the cave which was in it, with all the trees that
        were in the field, which were within all its surrounding boundaries\u2014passed  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'to Abraham as a property in the presence of the Hittites, with respect
        to all who were entering the gate of his city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And thus afterward Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the
        field of Machpelah near Mamre; that is Hebron, in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the field and the cave which was in it passed to Abraham as a
        burial site from the Hittites.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac and Rebekah'
      title: Isaac and Rebekah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Abraham was old, advanced in age, and Yahweh had blessed Abraham
        in everything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Abraham said to his servant, the oldest of his house, who had
        charge of all he had, \u201CPlease put your hand under my thigh "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'that I may make you swear by Yahweh, the God of heaven and the God
        of earth, that you will not take a wife for my son from the daughters of
        the Canaanites in whose midst I am dwelling, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "but that you will go to my land and to my family, and take a wife
        for my son, for Isaac.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the servant said to him, \u201CPerhaps the woman will not be
        willing to follow me to this land\u2014must I then return your son to the
        land from whence you came?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Abraham said to him, \u201CYou must take care that you do not return
        my son there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Yahweh, the God of heaven who took me from the house of my father
        and from the land of my family, and who spoke to me and swore to me, saying,
        \u2018to your offspring I will give this land,\u2019 he will send his angel
        before you, and you shall take a wife for my son from there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And if the woman is not willing to follow you, then you shall be
        released from this oath of mine\u2014only you must not return my son there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the servant put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master,
        and he swore to him concerning this matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the servant took ten camels from his master\u2019s camels, and
        he went with all kinds of his master\u2019s good things in his hand. And
        he arose and went to Aram-Naharaim, to the city of Nahor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And he made the camels kneel outside the city at the well of water,
        at the time of evening, toward the time the women went out to draw water.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u201CO Yahweh, God of my master Abraham, please grant
        me success today and show loyal love to my master Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, I am standing by the spring of water, and the daughters of
        the men of the city are going out to draw water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And let it be that the girl to whom I shall say, \u2018Please, offer
        your jar that I may drink\u2019 and who says, \u2018Drink\u2014and I will
        also water your camels,\u2019 she is the one you have chosen for your servant,
        for Isaac. By her I will know that you have shown loyal love to my master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And it happened that before he had finished speaking, behold, Rebekah\u2014who
        was born to Bethuel, son of Milcah, the wife of Nahor, the brother of Abraham\u2014came
        out, and her jar was on her shoulder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now the girl was very pleasing in appearance. She was a virgin; no
        man had known her. And she went down to the spring, filled her jar, and came
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the servant ran to meet her. And he said, \u201CPlease, let me
        drink a little of the water from your jar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And she said, \u201CDrink, my lord.\u201D And she quickly lowered
        her jar in her hand and gave him a drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When she finished giving him a drink she said, \u201CI will also
        draw water for your camels until they finish drinking.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And she quickly emptied her jar into the trough and ran again to
        the well to draw water. And she drew water for all his camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the man was gazing at her silently to know if Yahweh had made
        his journey successful or not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And it happened that as the camels finished drinking the man took
        a gold ring of a half shekel in weight and two bracelets for her arms, ten
        shekels in weight, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and said, \u201CPlease tell me, whose daughter are you? Is there
        a place at the house of your father for us to spend the night?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And she said to him, \u201CI am the daughter of Bethuel, son of Milcah,
        whom she bore to Nahor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then she said to him, \u201CWe have both straw and fodder in abundance,
        as well as a place to spend the night.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the man knelt down and worshiped Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said, \u201CBlessed be Yahweh, God of my master Abraham, who
        has not withheld his loyal love and his faithfulness from my master. I was
        on the way and Yahweh led me to the house of my master\u2019s brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then the girl ran and reported these things to the household of her
        mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now Rebekah had a brother, and his name was Laban. And Laban ran
        out to the man toward the spring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And when he saw the ring and the bracelets on the arms of his sister
        and heard the words of Rebekah his sister, who said, \u201CThus the man spoke
        to me,\u201D he went to the man. And behold, he was standing with the camels
        at the spring. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CCome, O blessed one of Yahweh. Why do you stand
        outside? Now I have prepared the house and a place for the camels.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the man came to the house and unloaded the camels. And he gave
        straw and fodder to the camels, and water to wash his feet and the feet of
        the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And food was placed before him to eat. And he said, \u201CI will
        not eat until I have told my errand.\u201D And he said, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And he said, \u201CI am the servant of Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Now Yahweh has blessed my master exceedingly, and he has become great.
        He has given to him sheep and cattle, silver and gold, male slaves and female
        slaves, and camels and donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Sarah, the wife of my master, has borne a son to my master after
        her old age. And he has given to him all that he has. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And my master made me swear, saying, \u2018Do not take a wife for
        my son from the daughters of the Canaanites in whose land I am living. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But you shall go to the house of my father, and to my family, and
        you shall take a wife for my son.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And I said to my master, \u2018Perhaps the woman will not follow
        me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And he said to me, \u2018Yahweh, before whom I have walked, shall
        send his angel with you and will make your journey successful. And you shall
        take a wife for my son from my family, and from the house of my father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then you shall be released from my oath, when you come to my family.
        And if they will not give a woman to you, then you will be released from
        my oath.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then today I came to the spring, and I said, \u2018O Yahweh, God
        of my master Abraham, if you would please make my journey successful, upon
        which I am going. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Behold, I am standing by the spring of water. Let it be that the
        young woman who comes out to draw water and to whom I say, \u201CPlease give
        me a little water to drink from your jar,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "let her say to me, \u201CDrink; I will also draw water for your camels,\u201D
        she is the woman whom Yahweh has appointed for the son of my master.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "I had not yet finished speaking to myself when, behold, Rebekah was
        coming out with her jar on her shoulder. And she went down to the spring
        and drew water. And I said to her, \u2018Please give me a drink.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And she hastened and let down her jar from her shoulder and said,
        \u2018Drink, and I will give a drink to your camels also.\u2019 Then I drank
        and she gave a drink to the camels also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then I asked her and said, \u2018Whose daughter are you?\u2019 And
        she said, \u2018The daughter of Bethuel, son of Nahor, whom Milcah bore to
        him.\u2019 And I put the ring on her nose and the bracelets on her arms. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And I knelt down and worshiped Yahweh, and I praised Yahweh, the
        God of my master Abraham, who led me on the right way, to take the daughter
        of the brother of my master for his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "So now, if you are going to deal loyally and truly with my master,
        tell me. And if not, tell me, so that I may turn to the right or to the left.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Then Laban and Bethuel answered, and they said, \u201CThe matter
        has gone out from Yahweh; we are not able to speak bad or good to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Here is Rebekah before you. Take her and go; let her be a wife for
        the son of your master as Yahweh has spoken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And it happened that when the servant of Abraham heard their words
        he bowed down to the ground to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And the servant brought out silver jewelry and gold jewelry, and
        garments, and he gave them to Rebekah. And he gave precious gifts to her
        brother and to her mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "And he and the men who were with him ate and drank, and they spent
        the night. And they got up in the morning, and he said, \u201CLet me go to
        my master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "And her brother and her mother said, \u201CLet the girl remain with
        us ten days or so; after that she may go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CDo not delay me. Now, Yahweh has made
        my journey successful. Let me go. I must go to my master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "And they said, \u201CLet us call the girl and ask her opinion.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "And they called Rebekah and said to her, \u201CWill you go with this
        man?\u201D And she said, \u201CI will go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'So they sent away Rebekah their sister, and her nurse, and the servant
        of Abraham and his men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "And they blessed Rebekah and said to her, \u201CYou are our sister;
        may you become countless thousands; and may your offspring take possession
        of the gate of his enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'And Rebekah and her maidservants arose, and they mounted the camels
        and followed the man. And the servant took Rebekah and left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Now Isaac was coming from the direction of Beer-Lahai-Roi. And he
        was living in the land of the Negev. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: "And Isaac went out to meditate in the field early in the evening,
        and he lifted up his eyes and saw\u2014behold, camels were coming. "
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'And Rebekah lifted up her eyes and saw Isaac. And she got down from
        the camel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "And she said to the servant, \u201CWho is this man walking around
        in the field to meet us?\u201D And the servant said, \u201CThat is my master.\u201D
        And she took her veil and covered herself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'And the servant told Isaac all the things that he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'And Isaac brought her to the tent of Sarah his mother. And he took
        Rebekah, and she became his wife. And Isaac loved her and was comforted after
        the death of his mother. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death and Descendants of Abraham'
      title: The Death and Descendants of Abraham
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Abraham again took a wife, and her name was Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And she bore to him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Jokshan fathered Sheba and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were
        Asshurim and Letushim and Leummim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abidah, and Eldaah.
        All of these were the children of Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Abraham gave all he had to Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But to the sons of Abraham\u2019s concubines Abraham gave gifts.
        And while he was still living he sent them away eastward, away from his son
        Isaac, to the land of the east. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now these are the days of the years of the life of Abraham: one hundred
        and seventy-five years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Abraham passed away and died in a good old age, old and full
        of years. And he was gathered to his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Isaac and Ishmael his sons buried him in the cave of Machpelah,
        in the field of Ephron, son of Zohar the Hittite, that was east of Mamre, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the field that Abraham had bought from the Hittites. There Abraham
        was buried and Sarah his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it happened that after the death of Abraham God blessed Isaac
        his son, and Isaac settled at Beer-Lahai-Roi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now these are the generations of Ishmael, the son of Abraham, that
        Hagar the Egyptian, the maidservant of Sarah, bore to Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And these are the names of the sons of Ishmael, by their names according
        to their family records. The firstborn of Ishmael was Nebaioth, then Kedar,
        Adbeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Hadad, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "These are the sons of Ishmael, and these are their names by their
        villages and by their encampments\u201412 leaders according to their tribes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now these are the years of the life of Ishmael: 137 years. And he
        passed away and died, and was gathered to his people.'
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Jacob and Esau'
      title: Jacob and Esau
      number: 18
      content: 'They settled from Havilah to Shur, which was opposite Egypt, going
        toward Asshur, opposite; he settled opposite all his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now these are the generations of Isaac, the son of Abraham. Abraham
        fathered Isaac, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah, the daughter
        of Bethuel the Aramean of Paddan-Aram, the sister of Laban the Aramean, as
        his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Isaac prayed to Yahweh on behalf of his wife, for she was barren.
        And Yahweh responded to his prayer, and Rebekah his wife conceived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the children in her womb jostled each other, and she said, \u201CIf
        it is going to be like this, why be pregnant?\u201D And she went to inquire
        of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Yahweh said to her, \u201CTwo nations are in your womb, and two
        peoples from birth shall be divided. And one people shall be stronger than
        the other. And the elder shall serve the younger.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when her days to give birth were completed, then\u2014behold\u2014twins
        were in her womb. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the first came out red, all his body was like a hairy coat, so
        they called his name Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And afterward his brother came out, and his hand grasped the heel
        of Esau, so his name was called Jacob. And Isaac was sixty years old at their
        birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the boys grew up. And Esau was a skilled hunter, a man of the
        field, but Jacob was a peaceful man, living in tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Isaac loved Esau because he could eat of his game, but Rebekah
        loved Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Once Jacob cooked a thick stew, and Esau came in from the field,
        and he was exhausted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Esau said to Jacob, \u201CGive me some of that red stuff to gulp
        down, for I am exhausted!\u201D (Therefore his name was called Edom). "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Jacob said, \u201CSell me your birthright first.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Esau said, \u201CLook, I am going to die; now what is this birthright
        to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Jacob said, \u201CSwear to me first.\u201D And he swore to him,
        and sold his birthright to Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Jacob gave Esau bread, and thick lentil stew, and he ate and
        drank. Then he got up and went away. So Esau despised his birthright. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac and Abimelech'
      title: Isaac and Abimelech
      number: 1
      content: 'And there was a famine in the land, besides the former famine which
        was in the days of Abraham. And Isaac went to Abimelech, king of the Philistines,
        to Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Yahweh appeared to him and said, \u201CDo not go down to Egypt;
        dwell in the land which I will show to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Dwell as an alien in this land, and I will be with you, and will
        bless you, for I will give all these lands to you and to your descendants,
        and I will establish the oath that I swore to Abraham you father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will multiply your descendants like the stars of heaven, and
        I will give to your descendants all these lands. And all nations of the earth
        will be blessed through your offspring, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "because Abraham listened to my voice and kept my charge: my commandments,
        my statutes, and my laws.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Isaac settled in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the men of the place asked concerning his wife, he said, \u201CShe
        is my sister,\u201D for he was afraid to say, \u201Cmy wife,\u201D thinking
        \u201Cthe men of the place will kill me on account of Rebekah, for she was
        beautiful.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And it happened that, when he had been there a long time, Abimelech
        the king of the Philistines looked through the window, and saw\u2014behold\u2014Isaac
        was fondling Rebekah his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Abimelech called Isaac and said, \u201CSurely she is your wife.
        Now why did you say \u2018She is my sister\u2019?\u201D And Isaac said to
        him, \u201CBecause I thought I would die on account of her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Abimelech said, \u201CWhat is this you have done to us? One of
        the people might easily have slept with your wife! Then you would have brought
        guilt upon us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Abimelech instructed all the people, saying, \u201CThe one who
        touches this man or his wife shall certainly die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Isaac sowed in that land and reaped in that same year a hundredfold,
        and Yahweh blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the man became wealthier and wealthier until he was exceedingly
        wealthy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he possessed sheep and cattle and many servants, so that the
        Philistines envied him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Philistines stopped up all the wells that the servants of
        his father had dug in the days of Abraham his father. They filled them with
        earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Abimelech said to Isaac, \u201CGo away from us, for you have
        become much too powerful for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Isaac departed from there and camped in the valley of Gerar, and
        settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Isaac dug again the wells of water which they had dug in the
        days of his father Abraham, which the Philistines had stopped up after the
        death of Abraham. And he gave to them the same names which his father had
        given them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And when the servants of Isaac dug in the valley, they found a well
        of fresh water there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the herdsmen of Gerar quarreled with the herdsmen of Isaac,
        saying, \u201CThe water is ours.\u201D And he called the name of the well
        Esek, because they contended with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they dug another well, and they quarreled over it also. And he
        called its name Sitnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then he moved from there and dug another well, and they did not quarrel
        over it. And he called its name Rehoboth, and said, \u201CNow Yahweh has
        made room for us, and we shall be fruitful in the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And from there he went up to Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Yahweh appeared to him that night and said, \u201CI am the God
        of your father Abraham. Do not be afraid, for I am with you, and I will bless
        you and make your descendants numerous for the sake of my servant Abraham.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he built an altar there and called on the name of Yahweh. And
        he pitched his tent there, and the servants of Isaac dug a well there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Abimelech went to him from Gerar with Ahuzzath his friend and
        Phicol his army commander. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Isaac said to them, \u201CWhy have you come to me? You hate me
        and sent me away from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And they said, \u201CWe see clearly that Yahweh has been with you,
        so we thought let there be an oath between us\u2014between us and you\u2014and
        let us make a covenant with you "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that you may not do us harm just as we have not touched you, but
        have only done good to you and sent you away in peace. You are now blessed
        by Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So he made a meal for them, and they ate and drank. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And they arose early in the morning and each one swore to the other,
        and Isaac sent them away. And they left him in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And it happened that on that same day the servants of Isaac came
        and told him about the well that they had dug. And they said, \u201CWe have
        found water!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he called it Sheba. Therefore the name of the city is Beersheba
        unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And when Esau was forty years old he took as wife Judith, daughter
        of Beeri the Hittite, and Basemath, daughter of Elon the Hittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And they made life bitter for Isaac and Rebekah. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob Steals Esau\u2019s Blessing"
      title: "Jacob Steals Esau\u2019s Blessing"
      number: 1
      content: "And it happened that when Isaac was old and his eyesight was weak,
        he called Esau his older son and said to him, \u201CMy son.\u201D And he
        said to him, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CLook, I am old; I do not know the day of my death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So now, take your weapons, your quiver and your bow, and go out to
        the field and hunt food for me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then make for me tasty food like I love, and bring it to me. And
        I will eat it so that I can bless you before I die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Rebekah was listening as Isaac spoke to Esau his son, and when
        Esau went to the field to hunt wild game to bring back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Rebekah said to Jacob her son, \u201CLook, I heard your father speaking
        to Esau your brother saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Bring wild game to me and prepare tasty food so I can eat it
        and bless you before Yahweh before my death.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So now, my son, listen to my voice, to what I command you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Go to the flock and take two good young goats from it for me, and
        I will prepare them as tasty food for your father, just as he likes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then you must take it to your father and he will eat it so that he
        may bless you before his death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jacob said to his mother, \u201CBehold, Esau my brother is a
        hairy man, but I am a smooth man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Perhaps my father will feel me and I will be in his eyes as a mocker,
        and he will bring upon me a curse and not a blessing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then his mother said to him, \u201CYour curse be upon me, my son,
        only listen to my voice\u2014go and get them for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So he went and took them, and brought them to his mother, and his
        mother prepared tasty food as his father liked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Rebekah took some of her older son Esau\u2019s best garments
        that were with her in the house, and she put them on Jacob her younger son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And she put the skins of the young goats over his hands and over the
        smooth part of his neck.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And she put the tasty food and the bread that she had made into the
        hand of Jacob, her son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he went to his father and said, \u201CMy father.\u201D And he
        said, \u201CHere I am. Who are you, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Jacob said to his father, \u201CI am Esau, your firstborn. I
        have done as you told me. Please get up, sit up and eat from my wild game
        so that you may bless me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Isaac said to his son, \u201CHow did you find it so quickly,
        my son?\u201D And he said, \u201CBecause Yahweh your God caused me to find
        it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Isaac said to Jacob, \u201CPlease, come near and let me feel
        you, my son. Are you really my son Esau or not?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Jacob drew near to Isaac his father. And he felt him and said,
        \u201CThe voice is the voice of Jacob, but the hands are the hands of Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he did not recognize him because his hands were hairy like the
        hands of Esau his brother. And he blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And he said, \u201CAre you really my son Esau?\u201D And he said,
        \u201CI am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBring it near to me that I may eat from the game
        of my son, so that I may bless you.\u201D And he brought it to him, and he
        ate. And he brought wine to him, and he drank. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then his father Isaac said to him, \u201CCome near and kiss me, my
        son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he drew near and kissed him. And he smelled the smell of his
        garments, and he blessed him and said, \u201CLook, the smell of my son is
        like the smell of a field that Yahweh has blessed! "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'May God give you of the dew of heaven and of the fatness of the earth,
        and abundance of grain and new wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Let peoples serve you, and nations bow down to you; Be lord of your
        brothers, and may the sons of your mother bow down to you. Cursed be those
        cursing you, and blessed be those blessing you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And as soon as Isaac had finished blessing Jacob, immediately after
        Jacob had gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, Esau his brother
        came back from his hunting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He too prepared tasty food and brought it to his father. And he said
        to his father, \u201CLet my father arise and eat from the wild game of his
        son, that you may bless me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Isaac his father said to him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D And he
        said, \u201CI am your son, your firstborn, Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Isaac trembled violently. Then he said, \u201CWho then was he
        that hunted wild game and brought it to me, and I ate it all before you came,
        and I blessed him? Moreover, he will be blessed!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "When Esau heard the words of his father he cried out with a great
        and exceedingly bitter cry of distress. And he said to his father, \u201CBless
        me as well, my father!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And he said, \u201CYour brother came in deceit and took your blessing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then he said, \u201CIsn\u2019t that why he is named Jacob? He has
        deceived me these two times. He took my birthright and, look, now he has
        taken my blessing!\u201D Then he said, \u201CHave you not reserved a blessing
        for me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Isaac answered and said to Esau, \u201CBehold, I have made him
        lord over you and I have given him all his brothers as servants, and with
        grain and wine I have sustained him. Now what can I do for you, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Esau said to his father, \u201CHave you only one blessing, my
        father? Bless me also, my father!\u201D And Esau lifted up his voice and
        wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Isaac his father answered and said to him, \u201CYour home shall
        be from the fatness of the land, and from the dew of heaven above. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'But by your sword you shall live, and you shall serve your brother.
        But it shall be that when free yourself you shall tear off his yoke from
        your neck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then Esau held a grudge against Jacob on account of the blessing
        with which his father had blessed him. And Esau said in his heart, \u201CThe
        days of mourning for my father are coming, then I will kill Jacob my brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "But the words of Esau her older son were told to Rebekah. And she
        sent and called for her younger son Jacob. And she said to him, \u201CLook,
        Esau your brother is consoling himself concerning you, intending to kill
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Now then, my son, listen to my voice; arise and flee to Haran to
        Laban my brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Stay with him a few days until the wrath of your brother has turned\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "until the anger of your brother turns from you and he has forgotten
        what you have done to him. Then I will send and bring you from there. Why
        should I lose the two of you in one day?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Then Rebekah said to Isaac, \u201CI loathe my life because of the
        Hittite women. If Jacob takes a wife from Hittite women like these, from
        the native women, what am I living for?\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Flees to Haran'
      title: Jacob Flees to Haran
      number: 1
      content: "Then Isaac called Jacob and blessed him. And he instructed him and
        said to him, \u201CYou must not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Arise, go to Paddan-Aram, to the house of Bethuel, your mother\u2019s
        father, and take for yourself a wife from there, from the daughters of Laban
        your mother\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now, may El-Shaddai bless you, and make you fruitful, and multiply
        you, so that you become an assembly of peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And may he give you the blessing of Abraham, to you and to your descendants
        with you, that you may take possession of the land of your sojourning, which
        God gave to Abraham.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Isaac sent Jacob away, and he went to Paddan-Aram, to Laban
        the son of Bethuel the Aramean, the brother of Rebekah, the mother of Jacob
        and Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob and sent him away to Paddan-Aram,
        to take for himself a wife from there, and he blessed him and instructed
        him, saying, \u201CYou must not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and that Jacob listened to his father and to his mother and went
        to Paddan-Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Esau saw that the daughters of Canaan were evil in the eyes
        of Isaac his father, '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jacob\u2019s Dream"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Dream"
      number: 9
      content: 'then Esau went to Ishmael and took Mahalath, the daughter of Ishmael,
        son of Abraham, sister of Nebaioth, as a wife, in addition to the wives he
        had. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Jacob went out from Beersheba and went to Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he arrived at a certain place and spent the night there, because
        the sun had set. And he took one of the stones of the place and put it under
        his head and slept at that place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he dreamed, and behold, a stairway was set on the earth, and
        its top touched the heavens. And behold, angels of God were going up and
        going down on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And behold, Yahweh was standing beside him, and he said, \u201CI
        am Yahweh, the God of Abraham your father, and the God of Isaac. The ground
        on which you were sleeping I will give to you and to your descendants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your descendants shall be like the dust of the earth, and you will
        spread out to the west, and to the east, and to the north and to the south.
        And all the families of the earth will be blessed through you and through
        your descendants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now behold, I am with you, and I will keep you wherever you go. And
        I will bring you to this land, for I will not leave you until I have done
        what I have promised to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Jacob awoke from his sleep and said, \u201CSurely Yahweh is
        indeed in this place and I did not know!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he was afraid and said, \u201CHow awesome is this place! This
        is nothing else than the house of God, and this is the gate of heaven!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Jacob rose early in the morning, and he took the stone that he
        had put under his head and set it up as a stone pillar, and poured oil on
        top of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he called the name of that place Bethel; however, the name of
        the city was formerly Luz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Jacob made a vow saying, \u201CIf God will be with me and protect
        me on this way that I am going, and gives me food to eat and clothing to
        wear, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and if I return in peace to the house of my father, then Yahweh will
        become my God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And this stone that I have set up as a pillar shall be the house
        of God, and of all that you give to me I will certainly give a tenth to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Flees to Haran'
      title: Jacob Flees to Haran
      number: 1
      content: 'And Jacob continued his journey and went to the land of the Easterners.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he looked, and behold, there was a well in the field, and behold,
        there were three flocks of sheep lying beside it, for out of that well the
        flocks were watered. And the stone on the mouth of the well was large. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when all the flocks were gathered there, they rolled away the
        stone from the mouth of the well. And they watered the sheep and returned
        the stone upon the mouth of the well to its place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Jacob said to them, \u201CMy brothers, where are you from?\u201D
        And they said, \u201CWe are from Haran.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CDo you know Laban, son of Nahor?\u201D
        And they said, \u201CWe know him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CIs he well?\u201D And they said, \u201CHe
        is well. Now look, Rachel his daughter is coming with the sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said, \u201CLook, it is still broad daylight; it is not the
        time for the livestock to be gathered. Give water to the sheep and go, pasture
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they said, \u201CWe are not able, until all the flocks are gathered.
        Then the stone is rolled away from the mouth of the well, and we water the
        sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'While he was speaking with them, Rachel came with the sheep which
        belonged to her father, for she was pasturing them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And it happened that, when Jacob saw Rachel, the daughter of Laban,
        his mother\u2019s brother, and the sheep of Laban, his mother\u2019s brother,
        Jacob drew near and rolled away the stone from the mouth of the well and
        watered the sheep of Laban, his mother\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Jacob kissed Rachel, and lifted up his voice and wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And Jacob told Rachel that he was the relative of her father, and
        that he was the son of Rebekah. And she ran and told her father.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it happened that when Laban heard the message about Jacob, the
        son of his sister, he ran to meet him. And he embraced him and kissed him,
        and brought him to his house. And he told Laban all these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Jacob\u2019s Marriages"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Marriages"
      number: 14
      content: "And Laban said to him, \u201CSurely you are my flesh and my bone!\u201D
        And he stayed with him a month. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CJust because you are my brother should
        you work for me for nothing? Tell me what your wage should be.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Laban had two daughters. The name of the older was Leah, and
        the name of the younger was Rachel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the eyes of Leah were dull, but Rachel was beautiful in form
        and appearance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Jacob loved Rachel and said, \u201CI will serve you seven years
        for Rachel your younger daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Laban said, \u201CBetter that I give her to you than I give
        her to another man. Stay with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jacob worked for Rachel seven years, but they were as a few days
        in his eyes because he loved her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Jacob said to Laban, \u201CGive me my wife, that I may go in
        to her, for my time is completed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Laban gathered all the men of the place and prepared a feast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And it happened that in the evening he took Leah his daughter and
        brought her to him, and he went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Laban gave Zilpah his female servant to her, to Leah his daughter
        as a female servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And it happened that in the morning, behold, it was Leah! And he
        said to Laban, \u201CWhat is this you have done to me? Did I not serve with
        you for Rachel? Now why did you deceive me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Laban said, \u201CIt is not the custom in our country to give
        the younger before the firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Complete the week of this one, then I will also give you the other,
        on the condition that you will work for me another seven years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Jacob did so. So he completed the week of this one, then he gave
        Rachel his daughter to him as a wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Laban gave Bilhah his female servant to Rachel his daughter as
        a female servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jacob\u2019s Children"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Children"
      number: 30
      content: 'Then he also went in to Rachel, and he loved Rachel more than Leah.
        And he served with him yet another seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When Yahweh saw that Leah was unloved he opened her womb, but Rachel
        was barren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Leah conceived and gave birth to a son, and she called his name
        Reuben, for she said, \u201CBecause Yahweh has noticed my misery, that I
        am unloved. Now my husband will love me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And she conceived again and gave birth to a son. And she said, \u201CIt
        is because Yahweh has heard that I am unloved that he gave me this son also.\u201D
        And she called his name Simeon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And she conceived again and gave birth to a son. Then she said, \u201CNow
        this time my husband will be joined to me, for I have borne him three sons.\u201D
        Therefore, she called his name Levi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And she conceived again and gave birth to a son. And she said, \u201CThis
        time I will praise Yahweh.\u201D Therefore she called his name Judah. And
        she ceased bearing children. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Children"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Children"
      number: 1
      content: "When Rachel saw that she could not bear children to Jacob, Rachel
        envied her sister. And she said to Jacob, \u201CGive me children\u2014if
        not, I will die!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jacob became angry with Rachel. And he said, \u201CAm I in the
        place of God, who has withheld from you the fruit of the womb?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then she said, \u201CHere is my servant girl Bilhah; go in to her
        that she may bear children as my surrogate. Then I will even have children
        by her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then she gave him Bilhah, her female servant, as a wife, and Jacob
        went in to her '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Bilhah conceived and gave birth to a son for Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Rachel said, \u201CGod has judged me, and has also heard my
        voice, and has given me a son.\u201D Therefore she called his name Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Bilhah, Rachel\u2019s servant, conceived again and bore a second
        son to Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Rachel said, \u201CI have struggled a mighty struggle with my
        sister and have prevailed.\u201D And she called his name Naphtali. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Leah saw that she had ceased bearing children, she took Zilpah
        her female servant and gave her to Jacob as a wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Zilpah, the female slave of Leah, bore a son to Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CGood fortune!\u201D And she called his name
        Gad. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Zilpah, Leah\u2019s female servant, bore a second son to Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CHow happy am I! For women have called me happy.\u201D
        So she called his name Asher. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And in the days of the wheat harvest, Reuben went and found mandrakes
        in the field and he brought them to Leah his mother. And Rachel said to Leah,
        \u201CPlease give me some of your son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And she said to her, \u201CIs your taking my husband such a small
        thing that you will also take the mandrakes of my son?\u201D Then Rachel
        said, \u201CThen he may sleep with you tonight in exchange for your son\u2019s
        mandrakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Jacob came in from the field in the evening, Leah went out to
        meet him. And she said, \u201CCome in to me, for I have hired you with my
        son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D And he slept with her that night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And God listened to Leah and she conceived and gave birth to a fifth
        son for Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CGod has given me my wage since I gave my servant
        girl to my husband.\u201D And she called his name Issachar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Leah conceived again and gave birth to a sixth son for Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Leah said, \u201CGod has endowed me with a good gift. This time
        my husband will acknowledge me, because I bore him six sons.\u201D And she
        called his name Zebulun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And afterward she gave birth to a daughter. And she called her name
        Dinah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then God remembered Rachel and listened to her, and God opened her
        womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And she conceived and gave birth to a son. And she said, \u201CGod
        has taken away my disgrace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Jacob\u2019s Prosperity"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Prosperity"
      number: 24
      content: "And she called his name Joseph, saying, \u201CYahweh has added to
        me another son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And it happened that as soon as Rachel had given birth to Joseph,
        Jacob said to Laban, \u201CSend me away that I may go to my place and my
        land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Give me my wives and my children for which I have served you, and
        let me go. For you yourself know my service that I have rendered to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But Laban said to him, \u201CPlease, if I have found favor in your
        eyes, I have learned by divination that Yahweh has blessed me because of
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said, \u201CName your wage to me and I will give it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CYou yourself know how I have served you
        and how your livestock have been with me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For you had little before me, and it has increased abundantly. And
        Yahweh has blessed you wherever I turned. So then, when shall I provide for
        my own family also?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat shall I give you?\u201D And Jacob said, \u201CDo
        not give me anything. If you will do this thing for me, I will again feed
        your flocks and keep them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Let me pass through all your flocks today, removing all the speckled
        and spotted sheep from them, along with every dark-colored sheep among the
        sheep, and the spotted and speckled among the goats. That shall be my wages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And my righteousness will answer for me later when you come concerning
        my wages before you. Every one that is not speckled or spotted among the
        goats, or dark-colored among the sheep shall be stolen if it is with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then Laban said, \u201CLook! Very well. It shall be according to
        your word.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But that day he removed the streaked and spotted male goats and all
        the speckled and spotted female goats, all that had white on it, and every
        dark-colored ram, and put them in the charge of his sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And he put a journey of three days between him and Jacob, and Jacob
        pastured the remainder of Laban\u2019s flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then Jacob took fresh branches of poplar, almond, and plane trees
        and peeled white strips on them, exposing the white which was on the branches. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And he set the branches that he had peeled in front of the flocks,
        in the troughs and in the water containers. And they were in heat when they
        came to drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And the flocks mated by the branches, so the flocks bore streaked,
        speckled, and spotted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And Jacob separated the lambs and turned the faces of the flocks
        toward the streaked and all the dark-colored in Laban\u2019s flocks. And
        he put his own herds apart, and did not put them with the flocks of Laban. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And whenever any of the stronger of the flocks were in heat, Jacob
        put the branches in full view of the flock in the troughs that they might
        mate among the branches. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "But with the more feeble of the flock he would not put them there.
        So the feebler were Laban\u2019s and the stronger were Jacob\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And the man became exceedingly rich and had large flocks, female
        slaves, male slaves, camels, and donkeys. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Flees from Laban'
      title: Jacob Flees from Laban
      number: 1
      content: "Now he heard the words of the sons of Laban, saying, \u201CJacob
        has taken all that our father has,\u201D and \u201CFrom that which was our
        father\u2019s he has gained all this wealth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Jacob saw the face of Laban and, behold, it was not like it
        had been in the past.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Yahweh said to Jacob, \u201CReturn to the land of your ancestors
        and to your family, and I will be with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to the field, to his flocks, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and he said to them, \u201CLook, I see the face of your father, that
        it is not like it has been toward me in the past. But the God of my father
        is with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now you yourselves know that I have served your father with all my
        strength, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and your father has cheated me and changed my wages ten times, but
        God has not allowed him to harm me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If thus he said, \u2018Speckled shall be your wage,\u2019 then all
        the flock bore speckled. And if he said, \u2018Streaked shall be your wage,\u2019
        then all the flock bore streaked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "God has taken away your father\u2019s livestock and given them to
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now it happened that at the time of the mating of the flock I lifted
        up my eyes and saw in a dream, and behold, the rams mounting the flock were
        streaked, speckled, and dappled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the angel of God said to me in the dream, \u2018Jacob,\u2019
        and I said, \u2018Here I am.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u2018Lift up your eyes and see\u2014all the rams mounting
        the flock are streaked, speckled, and dappled, for I have seen all that Laban
        is doing to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I am the God of Bethel where you anointed a stone pillar, where you
        made a vow to me. Now get up, go out from this land and return to the land
        of your birth.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Rachel and Leah answered and said to him, \u201CIs there yet
        a portion for us, and an inheritance in the house of our father? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Are we not regarded as foreigners by him, because he has sold us
        and completely consumed our money? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For all the wealth that God has taken away from our father, it belongs
        to us and to our sons. So now, all that God has said to you, do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Jacob got up and put his children and his wives on the camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he drove all his livestock and his possessions that he had acquired,
        the livestock of his possession that he had acquired in Paddan-Aram, in order
        to go to Isaac his father, to the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now Laban had gone to shear his sheep, and Rachel stole the idols
        that belonged to her father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jacob tricked Laban the Aramean by not telling him that he intended
        to flee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then he fled with all that he had, and arose and crossed the Euphrates
        and set his face toward the hill country of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And on the third day it was told to Laban that Jacob had fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then he took his kinsmen with him and pursued after him, a seven-day
        journey, and he caught up with him in the hill country of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And God came to Laban the Aramean in a dream at night and said to
        him, \u201CTake care that you not speak with Jacob, whether good or evil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Laban overtook Jacob. Now Jacob had pitched his tent in the hill
        country, and Laban and his kinsmen pitched their tents in the hill country
        of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CWhat have you done that you tricked
        me and have carried off my daughters like captives of the sword? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Why did you hide your intention to flee and trick me, and did not
        tell me so that I would have sent you away with joy and song and tambourine
        and lyre? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And why did you not give me opportunity to kiss my grandsons and
        my daughters goodbye? Now you have behaved foolishly by doing this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It is in my power to do harm to you, but the God of your father spoke
        to me last night saying, \u2018Take care from speaking with Jacob, whether
        good or evil.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now, you have surely gone because you desperately longed for the
        house of your father, but why did you steal my gods?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Jacob answered and said to Laban, \u201CBecause I was afraid,
        for I thought, \u2018Lest you take your daughters from me by force.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But with whomever you find your gods, he shall not live. In the presence
        of your kinsmen now identify what is with me that is yours and take it.\u201D
        Now Jacob did not know that Rachel had stolen them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Laban went into Jacob\u2019s tent and Leah\u2019s tent and the
        tent of the two female servants and did not find his gods. And he came out
        of Leah\u2019s tent and went into Rachel\u2019s tent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now Rachel had taken the idols and put them in the saddle bag of
        the camel and sat on them. And Jacob searched the whole tent thoroughly but
        did not find them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And she said to her father, \u201CLet there not be anger in the eyes
        of my lord, for I am not able to rise before you, for the way of women is
        with me. And he searched carefully and did not find the idols. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Jacob became angry and quarreled with Laban. Jacob answered
        and said to Laban, \u201CWhat is my offense? What is my sin that you pursued
        after me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For you have searched all my possessions and what did you find among
        all the possessions of my household? Set it before my kinsmen and your kinsmen
        that they may decide between the two of us! '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'These twenty years I was with you; your ewes and your female goats
        did not miscarry, and the rams of your flocks I did not eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "I brought no mangled carcass to you\u2014I bore its loss. From my
        hand you sought it, whether stolen by day or stolen by night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'There I was, during the day the heat consumed me, and the cold by
        night, and my sleep fled from my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'These twenty years I have been in your house. I served you fourteen
        years for your two daughters and six years for your flock, and you have changed
        my wages ten times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "If the God of my father, the God of Abraham and the Fear of Isaac
        had not been with me, indeed now you would have sent me away empty-handed.
        God saw my misery and the labor of my hands and rebuked you last night.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then Laban answered and said to Jacob, \u201CThe daughters are my
        daughters and the grandsons are my grandsons, and the flocks are my flocks,
        and all that you see, it is mine. Now, what can I do for these my daughters
        today, or for their children whom they have borne? "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "So now, come, let us make a covenant, you and I, and let it be a
        witness between me and you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And Jacob took a stone and set it up as a stone pillar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And Jacob said to his kinsmen, \u201CGather stones.\u201D And they
        took stones and made a pile of stones, and they ate there by the pile of
        stones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And Laban called it Jegar Sahadutha, but Jacob called it Galeed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then Laban said, \u201CThis pile of stones is a witness between me
        and you today.\u201D Therefore its name is called Galeed,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "and Mizpah, because he said, \u201CYahweh watch between me and you
        when we are out of sight of each other.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "If you mistreat my daughters, and if you take wives besides my daughters,
        when there is no man with us, see\u2014God is a witness between me and you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "And Laban said to Jacob, \u201CSee, this pile of stones, and see
        the pillar that I have set up between me and you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'This pile of stones is a witness, and the pillar is a witness, that
        I will not pass beyond this pile of stones to you, and that you will not
        pass beyond this pile of stones and this pillar to me intending harm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "May the God of Abraham and the God of Nahor, the God of their father
        judge between us.\u201D Then Jacob swore by the Fear of his father Isaac. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'And Jacob sacrificed a sacrifice on the hill, and he called his kinsmen
        to eat the meal. And they ate the meal and spent the night on the hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: ' And Laban arose early in the morning and kissed his grandsons and
        his daughters, and blessed them. Then Laban departed and returned to his
        homeland. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Fears Esau'
      title: Jacob Fears Esau
      number: 1
      content: 'And Jacob went on his way, and angels of God met him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when he saw them, Jacob said, \u201CThis is the camp of God!\u201D
        And he called the name of that place Mahanaim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jacob sent messengers before him to Esau his brother, to the
        land of Seir, the territory of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he instructed them, saying, \u201CThus you must say to my lord,
        to Esau, \u2018Thus says your servant Jacob, I have dwelled as an alien with
        Laban, and I have remained there until now. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I have acquired cattle, male donkeys, flocks, and male and female
        slaves, and I have sent to tell my lord, to find favor in your eyes.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the messengers returned to Jacob and said, \u201CWe came to your
        brother, to Esau, and he is coming to meet you, and four hundred men are
        with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Jacob was very frightened and distressed. So he divided the
        people, flocks, cattle, and camels that were with him into two companies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he thought, \u201CIf Esau comes to one company and destroys it,
        the remaining company will be able to escape.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Jacob said, \u201CO God of my father Abraham, and God of my
        father Isaac, O Yahweh, who said to me, \u2018Return to your land and to
        your family, and I will deal well with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I am not worthy of all the loyal love and all the faithfulness that
        you have shown your servant, for with only my staff I crossed this Jordan,
        and now I have become two camps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Please rescue me from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau,
        for I fear him, lest he come and attack mother and children alike. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now you yourself said, \u2018I will surely deal well with you and
        make your offspring as the sand of the sea that cannot be counted for abundance.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he lodged there that night. Then he took from what he had with
        him a gift for Esau his brother: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'two hundred female goats, twenty male goats, two hundred ewes, twenty
        rams, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'thirty milk camels with their young, forty cows, ten bulls, twenty
        female donkeys, and ten male donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he put them under the hand of his servants, herd by herd, and
        said to his servants, \u201CCross on ahead before me, and put some distance
        between herds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he instructed the foremost, saying, \u201CWhen Esau my brother
        comes upon you and asks you, saying, \u2018Whose are you and where are you
        going? To whom do these animals belong ahead of you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then you must say, \u2018To your servant, to Jacob. It is a gift
        sent to my lord, to Esau. Now behold, he is also coming after us.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he also instructed the second servant and the third, and everyone
        else who was behind the herds, saying, \u201CYou must speak to Esau according
        to this word when you find him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And moreover, you shall say, \u2018Look, your servant Jacob is behind
        us.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D For he thought, \u201CLet me appease him with the gift
        going before me, and afterward I will see his face. Perhaps he will show
        me favor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Jacob Wrestles with God'
      title: Jacob Wrestles with God
      number: 21
      content: 'So the gift passed on before him, but he himself spent that night
        in the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'That night he arose and took his two wives, his two female servants,
        and his eleven children and crossed the ford of the Jabbok. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he took them and sent them across the stream. Then he sent across
        all his possessions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Jacob remained alone, and a man wrestled with him until the breaking
        of the dawn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And when he saw that he could not prevail against him, he struck
        his hip socket, so that Jacob\u2019s hip socket was sprained as he wrestled
        with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLet me go, for dawn is breaking.\u201D But he
        answered, \u201CI will not let you go unless you bless me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CWhat is your name?\u201D And he said,
        \u201CJacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said, \u201CYour name shall no longer be called Jacob, but
        Israel, for you have struggled with God and with men and have prevailed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jacob asked and said, \u201CPlease tell me your name.\u201D
        And he said, \u201CWhy do you ask this\u2014for my name?\u201D And he blessed
        him there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Jacob called the name of the place Peniel which means \u201CI
        have seen God face to face and my life was spared.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the sun rose upon him as he passed Penuel, and he was limping
        because of his hip. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Therefore the Israelites do not eat the sinew of the sciatic nerve
        that is upon the socket of the hip unto this day, because he struck the socket
        of the thigh of Jacob at the sinew of the sciatic nerve. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Meets Esau and Settles at Shechem'
      title: Jacob Meets Esau and Settles at Shechem
      number: 1
      content: 'And Jacob lifted up his eyes and looked. And behold, Esau was coming
        and four hundred men were with him. And he divided the children among Leah
        and among Rachel, and among the two of his female servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he put the female slaves and their children first, then Leah
        and her children next, then Rachel with Joseph last. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he himself passed on before them and bowed down to the ground
        seven times until he came to his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Esau ran to meet him, and embraced him, and fell upon his neck
        and kissed him, and they wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Esau lifted up his eyes and saw the women and the children and
        said, \u201CWho are these with you?\u201D And he said, \u201CThe children
        whom God has graciously given your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the female servants drew near, they and their children, and
        they bowed down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Leah and her children drew near and bowed down, and afterward
        Joseph and Rachel drew near and they bowed down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat do you mean by all this company that I have
        met?\u201D Then he said, \u201CTo find favor in the eyes of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Esau said, \u201CI have enough my brother; keep what you have.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Jacob said, \u201CNo, please, if I have found favor in your eyes,
        you must take my gift from my hand, for then I have seen your face which
        is like seeing the face of God, and you have received me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Please take my gift which has been brought to you, for God has dealt
        graciously with me, and because I have enough.\u201D And he urged him, so
        he took it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLet us journey and go on, and I will go ahead
        of you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But he said to him, \u201CMy lord knows that the children are frail,
        and the flocks and the cattle which are nursing are a concern to me. Now
        if they drove them hard for a day all the flocks would die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Let my lord pass on before his servant and I will move along slowly
        at the pace of the livestock that are ahead of me, and at the pace of the
        children until I come to my lord in Seir.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Esau said, \u201CLet me leave some of my people with you.\u201D
        But he said, \u201CWhat need is there? Let me find favor in the eyes of my
        lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Esau turned that day on his way to Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But Jacob traveled on to Succoth, and he built for himself a house,
        and he made shelters for his livestock. Therefore he called the name of the
        place Succoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Jacob came safely to the city of Shechem which is in the land
        of Canaan, on his way from Paddan-Aram. And he camped before the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he bought a piece of land where he pitched his tent for one hundred
        pieces of money from the hand of the sons of Hamor, father of Shechem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And there he erected an altar and called it \u201CEl Elohe Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rape of Dinah and the Massacre at Shechem'
      title: The Rape of Dinah and the Massacre at Shechem
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Dinah the daughter of Leah, whom she had borne to Jacob, went
        out to see the daughters of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Shechem, the son of Hamor the Hivite, the prince of the land,
        saw her. And he took her and lay with her and raped her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And his soul clung to Dinah, the daughter of Jacob, and he loved
        the girl and spoke tenderly to the girl. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Shechem said to Hamor his father, saying, \u201CGet this girl
        for me as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Jacob heard that Dinah his daughter had been defiled, but his
        sons were with his flocks in the field. And Jacob kept silent until they
        came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Hamor, father of Shechem, went out to Jacob to speak with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the sons of Jacob came in from the field when they heard it.
        And the men were distressed and very angry because he had done a disgraceful
        thing in Israel by having sexual relations with the daughter of Jacob\u2014something
        that should not be done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Hamor spoke with them saying, \u201CShechem my son is in love
        with your daughter. Please give her to him for a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Make marriages with us. Give us your daughters and take our daughters
        for yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You shall dwell with us and the land shall be before you; settle
        and trade in it, and acquire property in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Shechem said to her father and to her brothers, \u201CLet me
        find favor in your eyes, and whatever you say to me I will do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Make the bride price and gift as high as you like; I will give what
        you say to me. But give me the girl as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the sons of Jacob answered Shechem and his father Hamor speaking
        deceitfully, because he had defiled Dinah their sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And they said to them, \u201CWe cannot do this thing, to give our
        sister to a man who is uncircumcised, for that is a disgrace for us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Only on this condition will we give consent to you; if you will become
        like us\u2014every male among you to be circumcised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then we will give our daughters to you, and we will take for ourselves
        your daughters, and we will live with you and become one family. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you will not listen to us, to be circumcised, then we will
        take our daughters and we will go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And their words were good in the eyes of Hamor and in the eyes of
        Shechem, the son of Hamor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the young man did not delay to do the thing, for he wanted the
        daughter of Jacob. Now he was the most honored of his father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Hamor and his son Shechem came to the gate of their city, and
        they spoke to the men of their city, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThese men are at peace with us. Let them dwell in the land
        and let them trade in it. Now, behold, the land is broad enough for them.
        Let us take their daughters as wives, and let us give our daughters to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Only on this condition will they give consent to us, to live with
        us and to become one family\u2014when every male among us is circumcised
        as they are circumcised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Will not their livestock and their property and all their animals
        be ours? Only let us give consent to them so they will live among us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And all those who went out of the gate of his city listened to Hamor
        and Shechem. Every male was circumcised, all those who went out of the gate
        of his city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And it happened that on the third day, while they were in pain, two
        of the sons of Jacob, Simeon and Levi, the brothers of Dinah, each took his
        sword and came against the unsuspecting city and killed all the males. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They killed Hamor and his son Shechem with the edge of the sword,
        and they took Dinah from the house of Shechem and went out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The other sons of Jacob came upon the slain and plundered the city,
        because they had defiled their sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They took their flocks and their cattle and their donkeys, and whatever
        was in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "They captured and plundered all that was in the houses\u2014all their
        wealth, their little ones, and their women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, \u201CYou have brought trouble
        on me, making me stink among the inhabitants of the land, among the Canaanites
        and the Perizzites! I am few in number! If they gather against me and attack
        me, I will be destroyed\u2014I and my household!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But they said, \u201CShall he treat our sister like a prostitute?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Goes Back to Bethel'
      title: Jacob Goes Back to Bethel
      number: 1
      content: "And God said to Jacob, \u201CArise, go up to Bethel and dwell there,
        and make an altar to the God who appeared to you when you fled from before
        Esau your brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him, \u201CGet
        rid of the foreign gods that are in your midst and purify yourselves and
        change your garments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then let us make ready and let us go up to Bethel, so that I can
        make an altar there to the God who answered me in the day of my trouble,
        and who has been with me on the way that I have gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they gave to Jacob all the foreign gods that were in their hands,
        and the ornamental rings that were in their ears. And Jacob buried them under
        the oak which was near Shechem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then they set out on their journey, and the terror of God was upon
        the cities that were all around them, so that they did not pursue after the
        sons of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Jacob came to Luz which was in the land of Canaan (that is Bethel),
        he and all the people that were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he built an altar there and called the place El-Bethel, for there
        God had appeared to him when he fled before his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Deborah, the nurse of Rebekah, died. And she was buried below
        Bethel, under the oak. And its name was called Allon-Bacuth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And God appeared to Jacob again when he came from Paddan-Aram, and
        he blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And God said to him, \u201CYour name is Jacob. Your name shall no
        longer be called Jacob, but Israel shall be your name.\u201D Then his name
        was called Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And God said to him, \u201CI am El-Shaddai. Be fruitful and multiply.
        A nation and an assemblage of nations shall be from you, and kings shall
        go out from your loins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And as for the land that I gave to Abraham and to Isaac, I will give
        it to you. And to your descendants after you I will give the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And God went up from him at the place where he spoke with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Jacob set up a pillar at the place where God had spoken with
        him, a pillar of stone. And he poured out a drink offering upon it, and poured
        oil on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Death of Rachel'
      title: The Death of Rachel
      number: 15
      content: 'And Jacob called the name of the place where God had spoken with
        him Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then they journeyed from Bethel. And when they were still some distance
        from Ephrath, Rachel went into labor. And she had hard labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And when her labor was the most difficult the midwife said to her,
        \u201CDo not be afraid for you have another son.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And it happened that when her life was departing (for she was dying),
        she called his name Ben-Oni. But his father called him Benjamin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Rachel died and she was buried on the way to Ephrath (that is,
        Bethlehem). '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jacob erected a pillar at her burial site. That is the pillar
        of the burial site of Rachel unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Israel journeyed on and pitched his tent beyond the tower of
        Eder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Twelve Sons of Jacob'
      title: The Twelve Sons of Jacob
      number: 22
      content: "And while Israel was living in that land Reuben went and had sexual
        relations with Bilhah, his father\u2019s concubine. And Israel heard about
        it. Now the sons of Jacob were twelve. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Leah: The firstborn of Jacob was Reuben. Then Simeon,
        Levi, Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Rachel: Joseph and Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sons of Bilhah, the female servant of Rachel: Dan and Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: The Death of Isaac'
      title: The Death of Isaac
      number: 26
      content: 'The sons of Zilpah, the female servant of Leah: Gad and Asher. These
        were the sons of Jacob who were born to him in Paddan-Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Jacob came to Isaac his father at Mamre, or Kiriath-Arba (that
        is, Hebron), where Abraham and Isaac dwelled as aliens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the days of Isaac were one hundred and eighty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Isaac passed away and died, and was gathered to his people, old
        and full of days. And his sons Esau and Jacob buried him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Descendants of Esau'
      title: The Descendants of Esau
      number: 1
      content: 'Now these are the descendants of Esau (that is, Edom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Esau took his wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah, daughter
        of Elon, the Hittite, and Oholibamah, daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon,
        the Hivite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and Basemath, the daughter of Ishmael, the sister of Nebaioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Adah bore to Esau Eliphaz; and Basemath bore Reuel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Oholibamah bore Jeush and Jalam, and Korah. These are the sons
        of Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Esau took his wives and his sons and his daughters, and all the
        persons of his household, and his sheep and goats, and all his cattle, and
        all the goods that he had acquired in the land of Canaan, and went to a land
        away from his brother Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For their possessions were too many to live together, so that the
        land of their sojourning was not able to support them on account of their
        livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Esau dwelled in the hill country of Seir (Esau, that is Edom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now these are the descendants of Esau, the father of Edom, in the
        hill country of Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'These are the names of the sons of Esau: Eliphaz, the son of Adah,
        the wife of Esau; Reuel, the son of Basemath, the wife of Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '(Now Timnah was the concubine of Eliphaz, the son of Esau. And she
        bore Amalek to Eliphaz.) These are the sons of Adah, the wife of Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now these are the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.
        These are the sons of Basemath, the wife of Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now these are the sons of Oholibamah, the daughter of Anah, daughter
        of Zibeon, the wife of Esau: She bore to Esau Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the chiefs of the sons of Esau. The sons of Eliphaz, the
        firstborn of Esau: the chiefs of Teman, Omar, Zepho, Kenaz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Korah, Gatam, and Amalek. These are the chiefs of Eliphaz in the
        land of Edom. These are the sons of Adah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now these are the sons Reuel, the son of Esau: the chiefs Nahath,
        Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These are the chiefs of Reuel in the land of
        Edom. These are the sons of Basemath, the wife of Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now these are the sons of Oholibamah, the wife of Esau: the chiefs
        Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. These are the chiefs born of Oholibamah, the daughter
        of Anah, the wife of Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These are the sons of Esau, and these are their chiefs (that is,
        Edom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'These are the sons of Seir, the Horite, the inhabitants of the land:
        Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These are the chiefs of the Horites, the
        sons of Seir in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam. And Lotan\u2019s sister
        was Timna. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now these are the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho,
        and Onam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Now these are the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah\u2014he is Anah who
        found the hot springs in the desert while he pastured the donkeys of Zibeon
        his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now these are the sons of Anah: Dishon and Oholibamah, the daughter
        of Anah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now these are the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Keran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'These are the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'These are the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These are the chiefs of the Horites: the chiefs Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon,
        Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Kings of Edom'
      title: The Kings of Edom
      number: 30
      content: 'Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These are the chiefs of the Horites, according
        to their chiefs in the land of Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now these are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any
        king ruled over the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom. And the name of his city was
        Dinhabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Bela died, and Jobab, the son of Zerah from Bozrah, reigned in
        his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Jobab died, and Husham from the land of the Temanites reigned
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And Husham died, and Hadad, son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in
        the field of Moab reigned in his place. And the name of his city was Avith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Hadad died, and Samlah from Masrekah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And Samlah died, and Shaul from Rehoboth on the Euphrates reigned
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And Shaul died, and Baal-Hanan, the son of Acbor, reigned in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And Baal-Hanan the son of Acbor died, and Hadar reigned in his place.
        And the name of his city was Pau, and the name of his wife was Mehetabel,
        the daughter of Matred, daughter of Mezahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Now these are the names of the chiefs of Esau according to their
        families, according to their dwelling places, by their names: the chiefs
        Timna, Alvah, Jetheth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Magdiel, and Iram. These are the chiefs of Edom (that is, Esau, the
        father of Edom) according to their settlements in the land of their possession. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Dreams of Joseph'
      title: The Dreams of Joseph
      number: 1
      content: 'And Jacob settled in the land of the sojourning of his father, in
        the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'These are the generations of Jacob. Joseph, being seventeen years
        old, was shepherding the flock with his brothers. Now he was a helper with
        the sons of Bilhah and the sons of Zilpah, the wives of his father. And Joseph
        brought a bad report of them to his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Israel loved Joseph more than all his sons, for he was a son
        of his old age. And he made a robe with long sleeves for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When his brothers saw that their father loved him more than all his
        brothers, they hated him and were not able to speak peaceably to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Joseph dreamed a dream, and he told it to his brothers. And they
        hated him even more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CListen now to this dream that I dreamed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now behold, we were binding sheaves in the midst of the field and,
        behold, my sheaf stood up and it remained standing. Then behold, your sheaves
        gathered around and bowed down to my sheaf.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then his brothers said to him, \u201CWill you really rule over us?\u201D
        And they hated him even more on account of his dream and because of his words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then he dreamed yet another dream and told it to his brothers. And
        he said, \u201CBehold, I dreamed a dream again, and behold, the sun and the
        moon and eleven stars were bowing down to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he told it to his father and to his brothers. And his father
        rebuked him and said to him, \u201CWhat is this dream that you have dreamed?
        Will I and your mother and your brothers indeed come to bow down to the ground
        to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Joseph Sold Into Slavery by his Brothers'
      title: Joseph Sold Into Slavery by his Brothers
      number: 11
      content: 'And his brothers were jealous of him, but his father kept the matter
        in mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now his brothers went to pasture the flock of their father in Shechem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CAre not your brothers pasturing
        in Shechem? Come, let me send you to them.\u201D And he said, \u201CHere
        I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CGo now, see if it goes well for your brothers
        and for the flock, then return word to me.\u201D And he sent him from the
        valley of Hebron, and he arrived at Shechem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And a man found him, and behold, he was wandering about in a field.
        And the man asked him, \u201CWhat do you seek?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CI am seeking my brothers. Tell me, please, where
        they are pasturing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the man said, \u201CThey have moved on from here, for I heard
        them saying, \u2018Let us go to Dothan.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D Then Joseph went
        after his brothers and found them in Dothan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they saw him from a distance. And before he drew near to them,
        they conspired against him to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And each said to his brothers, \u201CLook, this master of dreams
        is coming. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now then, come, let us kill him and throw him in one of the pits.
        Then we will say a wild animal devoured him. Then we will see what his dreams
        become.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Reuben heard it and delivered him from their hand and said, \u201CWe
        must not take his life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Reuben said to them, \u201CYou must not shed blood. Throw him
        into this pit that is in the desert, but do not lay a hand on him\u201D\u2014so
        that he might rescue him from their hand to return him to his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And it happened that as Joseph came to his brothers they stripped
        Joseph of his robe, the robe with long sleeves, that was upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they took him and threw him into the pit (the pit was empty;
        there was no water in it). '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they sat down to eat some food. And they lifted up their eyes
        and looked, and behold, a caravan of Ishmaelites was coming from Gilead.
        And their camels were carrying aromatic gum and balm and spices on the way
        to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Judah said to his brothers, \u201CWhat profit is there if we
        kill our brother and conceal his blood? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Come, let us sell him to the Ishmaelites, but our hand shall not
        be against him, for he is our brother, our own flesh.\u201D And his brothers
        agreed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Midianite traders passed by. And they drew Joseph up and brought
        him up from the pit, and they sold Joseph to the Ishmaelites for twenty pieces
        of silver. And they brought Joseph to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Reuben returned to the pit and, behold, Joseph was not in the
        pit. And he tore his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he returned to his brothers and said, \u201CThe boy is gone!
        Now I, what can I do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then they took the robe of Joseph and slaughtered a goat, and dipped
        the robe in the blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then they sent the robe with long sleeves and they brought it to
        their father and said, \u201CWe found this; please examine it. Is it the
        robe of your son or not?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And he recognized it and said, \u201CThe robe of my son! A wild animal
        has devoured him! Joseph is surely torn to pieces!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Jacob tore his clothes and put sackcloth on his loins and mourned
        for his son many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And all his sons and daughters tried to console him, but he refused
        to be consoled. And he said, \u201CNo, I shall go down to my son, to Sheol,
        mourning.\u201D And his father wept for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And the Midianites sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, a court official
        of Pharaoh, a commander of the imperial guard. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah and Tamar'
      title: Judah and Tamar
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that at that time Judah went down from his brothers
        and pitched his tent near a certain Adullamite, whose name was Hirah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Judah saw the daughter of a certain Canaanite there whose name
        was Shua. And he took her and went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And she conceived and bore a son, and he called his name Er. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And she conceived again and bore a son, and he called his name Onan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And once again she bore a son, and she called his name Shelah. And
        he was in Chezib when she bore him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name was Tamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Er, the firstborn of Judah, was evil in the eyes of Yahweh, and
        Yahweh killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Judah said to Onan, \u201CGo in to the wife of your brother
        and perform the duty of a brother-in-law to her, and raise up offspring for
        your brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But Onan knew that the offspring would not be for him, so whenever
        he went in to the wife of his brother he would waste it on the ground so
        as not to give offspring to his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And what he did was evil in the sight of Yahweh, so he killed him
        also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Judah said to Tamar, his daughter-in-law, \u201CStay a widow
        in your father\u2019s house until Shelah my son grows up,\u201D for he feared
        he would also die like his brother. So Tamar went and stayed in the house
        of her father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And in the course of time the daughter of Shua, the wife of Judah,
        died. When Judah was consoled he went up to his sheepshearers, he and his
        friend Hirah the Adullamite, to Timnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it was told to Tamar, saying, \u201CLook, your father-in-law
        is going up to Timnah to shear his sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So she removed the clothes of her widowhood and covered herself with
        the veil and disguised herself. And she sat at the entrance to Eynayim, which
        is on the way to Timnah, for she saw that Shelah was grown but she had not
        been given to him as a wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Judah saw her and reckoned her to be a prostitute, for she had
        covered her face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he turned aside to her at the roadside and said, \u201CPlease
        come, let me come in to you,\u201D for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law.
        And she said, \u201CWhat will you give to me that you may come in to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CI will send a kid from the goats of the flock.\u201D
        And she said, \u201COnly if you give a pledge until you send it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat is the pledge that I must give to you?\u201D
        And she said, \u201Cyour seal, your cord, and your staff that is in your
        hand.\u201D And he gave them to her and went in to her. And she conceived
        by him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And she arose and left, and she removed her veil from herself and
        put on the garments of her widowhood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Judah sent the kid from the goats by the hand of his friend the
        Adullamite to take back the pledge from the hand of the woman, but he could
        not find her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So he asked the men of her place, saying, \u201CWhere is that cult
        prostitute that was at Eynayim by the roadside?\u201D And they said, \u201CThere
        is no cult prostitute here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then he returned to Judah and said, \u201CI could not find her. Morever,
        the men of the place said, \u2018There is no cult prostitute here.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Judah said, \u201CLet her take them for herself, lest we be laughed
        at. Behold, I sent this kid, but you could not find her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And about three months later it was told to Judah, \u201CTamar your
        daughter-in-law has played the whore, and now, behold, she has conceived
        by prostitution.\u201D And Judah said, \u201CBring her out and let her be
        burned.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "She was brought out, but she sent to her father-in-law saying, \u201CBy
        the man to whom these belong I have conceived.\u201D And she said, \u201CNow
        discern to whom these belong: the seal and cord and the staff.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Judah recognized them and said, \u201CShe is more righteous
        than I, since I did not give her to my son Shelah.\u201D And he did not know
        her again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And it happened that at the time she gave birth that, behold, twins
        were in her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And it happened that at her labor one child put out a hand. And the
        midwife took it and tied a crimson thread on his hand saying, \u201CThis
        one came out first.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then his hand drew back and, behold, his brother came out, and she
        said, \u201CWhat a breach you have made for yourself!\u201D And she called
        his name Perez. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And afterward his brother who had the crimson thread on his hand
        came out. And his name was called Zerah. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph in Potiphar\u2019s House"
      title: "Joseph in Potiphar\u2019s House"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Joseph had been brought down to Egypt, and Potiphar, a court
        official of Pharaoh, commander of the guard, an Egyptian, bought him from
        the hand of the Ishmaelites who had brought him down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Yahweh was with Joseph, and he became a successful man. And he
        was in the house of his master, the Egyptian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And his master observed that Yahweh was with him, and everything
        that was in his hand to do Yahweh made successful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Joseph found favor in his eyes and he served him. Then he appointed
        him over his house and all that he owned he put into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it happened that from the time he appointed him over his house
        and over all that he had, Yahweh blessed the house of the Egyptian on account
        of Joseph. And the blessing of Yahweh was upon all that he had in the house
        and in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he left all that he had in the hand of Joseph, and he did not
        worry about anything except the food that he ate. Now Joseph was well built
        and handsome.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And it happened that after these things his master\u2019s wife cast
        her eyes on Joseph, and she said, \u201CLie with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But he refused and said to his master\u2019s wife, \u201CLook, my
        master does not worry about what is in the house, and everything he owns
        he has put in my hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He has no greater authority in this house than me, and he has not
        withheld anything from me except you, since you are his wife. Now how could
        I do this great wickedness and sin against God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And it happened that as she spoke to Joseph day after day, he did
        not heed her to lie beside her or to be with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But one particular day he came into the house to do his work and
        none of the men of the house were there in the house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "she seized him by his garment and said, \u201CLie with me!\u201D
        And he left his garment in her hand and fled, and he went outside. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it happened that when she saw that he left his garment in her
        hand and fled outside, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "she called to the men of her house and said to them, \u201CLook!
        He brought a Hebrew man to us to mock us! He came to me to lie with me, and
        I cried out with a loud voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when he heard me, that I raised my voice and called out, he left
        his garment beside me and fled, and he went outside.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then she put his garment beside her until his master came to his
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then she spoke to him according to these words, saying, \u201CThe
        Hebrew slave that you brought to us came to me to make fun of me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And it happened that as I raised my voice and called out, he left
        his garment beside me and fled outside.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when his master heard the words of his wife that she spoke to
        him, \u201CThis is what your servant did to me,\u201D he became very angry.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Joseph\u2019s master took him and put him into prison, the place
        that the king\u2019s prisoners were confined. And he was there in prison. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Yahweh was with Joseph, and showed loyal love to him, and gave
        him favor in the eyes of the chief of the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the chief of the prison put all the prisoners that were in the
        prison into the hand of Joseph. And everything that was done there, he was
        the one who did it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The chief of the prison did not worry about anything in his hand,
        since Yahweh was with him. And whatever he did Yahweh made it successful. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Interprets Dreams in Prison'
      title: Joseph Interprets Dreams in Prison
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that after these things the cupbearer of the king
        of Egypt and his baker did wrong against their lord, against the king of
        Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Pharaoh was angry with his two officials, with the chief cupbearer
        and chief baker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he put them in custody in the house of the chief of the guard,
        into the prison where Joseph was confined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the chief of the guard appointed Joseph to be with them, and
        he attended them. And they were in custody many days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the two of them, the cupbearer and the baker of the king of Egypt,
        who were confined in the prison, dreamed a dream, each his own dream, with
        its own interpretation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Joseph came to them in the morning he looked at them, and behold,
        they were troubled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he asked the court officials of Pharaoh that were with him in
        the custody of his master\u2019s house, \u201CWhy are your faces sad today?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWe each dreamed a dream, but there is
        no one to interpret it.\u201D And Joseph said to them, \u201CDo not interpretations
        belong to God? Please tell them to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the chief cupbearer told his dream to Joseph, and he said to
        him, \u201CIn my dream, now behold, there was a vine before me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and on the vine were three branches. And as it budded, its blossoms
        came up, and its clusters of grapes grew ripe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the cup of Pharaoh was in my hand, and I took the grapes and
        squeezed them into the cup of Pharaoh. Then I placed the cup into the hand
        of Pharaoh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joseph said to him, \u201CThis is its interpretation: The three
        branches, they are three days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In three days Pharaoh will lift up your head and will restore you
        to your office. And you shall put the cup of Pharaoh into his hand as was
        formerly the custom, when you were his cupbearer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But remember me when it goes well with you, and please may you show
        kindness with respect to me, and mention me to Pharaoh, and bring me out
        of this house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For I was surely kidnapped from the land of the Hebrews, and here
        also I have done nothing that they should put me in this pit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good he
        said to Joseph, \u201CI also dreamed. In my dream, now behold, there were
        three baskets of bread upon my head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And in the upper basket were all sorts of baked foods for Pharaoh,
        but the birds were eating them out of the basket upon my head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Joseph answered and said, \u201CThis is its interpretation:
        The three baskets, they are three days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "In three days Pharaoh will lift your head from you and hang you on
        a pole, and the birds will eat your flesh from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And it happened that on the third day, which was Pharaoh\u2019s birthday,
        he made a feast for all his servants. And he lifted up the head of the chief
        cupbearer and the head of the chief baker in the midst of his servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And he restored the chief cupbearer to his cupbearing position. And
        he placed the cup in the hand of Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the chief baker he hanged as Joseph had interpreted to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the chief cupbearer did not remember Joseph, but forgot him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph Interprets Pharaoh\u2019s Dreams"
      title: "Joseph Interprets Pharaoh\u2019s Dreams"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that after two full years Pharaoh dreamed, and behold,
        he was standing by the Nile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And behold, seven cows, well built and fat, were coming up from the
        Nile, and they grazed among the reeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And behold, seven other cows came up after them from the Nile, ugly
        and gaunt, and they stood beside those cows on the bank of the Nile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the ugly and gaunt cows ate the seven well built and fat cows.
        Then Pharaoh awoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he fell asleep and dreamed a second time, and behold, seven ears
        of grain, plump and good, were coming out of one stalk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And behold, seven thin ears of grain, scorched by the east wind,
        sprouted up after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the thin ears of grain swallowed up the seven plump and full
        ears of grain. Then Pharaoh awoke, and behold, it was a dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it happened that in the morning his spirit was troubled, and
        he sent and called all of the magicians of Egypt, and all its wise men, and
        Pharaoh told his dream to them. But they had no interpretation for Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the chief of the cupbearers spoke with Pharaoh, saying, \u201CI
        remember my sins today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Pharaoh was angry with his servants, and he put me and the chief
        baker in the custody of the house of the chief of the guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And we dreamed a dream one night, I and he, each with a dream that
        had a meaning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And there with us was a young man, a Hebrew servant of the chief
        of the guard, and we told him the dream, and he interpreted our dreams for
        us, each according to his dream he interpreted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it happened just as he interpreted to us, so it was. He restored
        me to my office, and him he hanged.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Pharaoh sent and called for Joseph, and they brought him quickly
        from the prison. And he shaved and changed his clothing, and came to Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CI dreamed a dream, but there is
        none to interpret it. Now, I have heard concerning you that when you hear
        a dream you can interpret it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Joseph answered Pharaoh saying, \u201CIt is not in my power;
        God will answer concerning the well-being of Pharaoh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CNow in my dream, behold, I was
        standing on the bank of the Nile, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and behold, seven cows, well built and fat, were coming up from the
        Nile, and they grazed among the reeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And behold, seven other cows came up after them from the Nile, very
        ugly and gaunt\u2014never have I seen any as them in all the land of Egypt
        for ugliness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the thin and ugly cows ate the former seven healthy cows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But when they went into their bellies it could not be known that
        they went into their bellies, for their appearance was as ugly as at the
        beginning. Then I awoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then I saw in my dream and behold, seven ears of grain were coming
        out of one stalk, full and good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And behold, seven withered ears of grain, thin and scorched by the
        east wind, sprouted up after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the thin ears of grain swallowed up the seven good ears of grain.
        And I told the magicians, but there was none to explain it to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe dreams of Pharaoh are one.
        God has revealed to Pharaoh what he is about to do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The seven good cows, they are seven years, and the seven good ears
        of grain, they are seven years. The dreams are one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the seven thin and ugly cows coming up after them, they are seven
        years, and the seven empty ears of grain, scorched by the east wind, they
        are also seven years of famine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the word that I have spoken to Pharaoh; God has shown Pharaoh
        what he is about to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Behold, seven years of great abundance are coming throughout the
        whole land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then seven years of famine will arise after them, and all the abundance
        in the land of Egypt will be forgotten. The famine will consume the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Abundance in the land will not be known because of the famine that
        follows, for it will be very heavy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now concerning the repetition of the dream twice to Pharaoh, it is
        because the matter is established by God, and God will do it quickly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now then, let Pharaoh select a man who is discerning and wise, and
        let him set him over the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Let Pharaoh do this, and let him appoint supervisors over the land,
        and let him take one-fifth from the land of Egypt in the seven years of abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then let them gather all the food of these coming good years and
        let them pile up grain under the hand of Pharaoh for food in the cities,
        and let them keep it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Joseph Rises to Power'
      title: Joseph Rises to Power
      number: 36
      content: "Then the food shall be as a deposit for the land for the seven years
        of the famine that will be in the land of Egypt, that the land will not perish
        on account of the famine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the plan was good in the eyes of Pharaoh and in the eyes of all
        his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to his servants, \u201CCan we find a man like this
        in whom is the spirit of God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSince God has made all of this
        known to you there is no one as discerning and wise as you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "You shall be over my house, and to your word all my people shall
        submit. Only with respect to the throne will I be greater than you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSee, I have set you over all the
        land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Then Pharaoh removed his signet ring from his finger and put it on
        the finger of Joseph. And he clothed him with garments of fine linen, and
        he put a chain of gold around his neck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And he had him ride in his second chariot. And they cried out before
        him, \u201CKneel!\u201D And Pharaoh set him over all the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CI am Pharaoh, but without your
        consent no one will lift his hand or his foot in all the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And Pharaoh called the name of Joseph Zaphenath-paneah and gave him
        Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera, priest of On, as a wife. And Joseph went
        out over the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Now Joseph was thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh, the
        king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh and traveled
        through the whole land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And the land produced a plenty in the seven years of abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And he gathered all the food of the seven years which occurred in
        the land of Egypt. And he stored the food in the cities. The food of the
        field that surrounded each city he stored in its midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'And Joseph piled up grain like the sand of the sea in great abundance
        until he stopped counting it, for it could not be counted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Before the years of famine came, Asenath, daughter of Potiphera priest
        of On, bore two sons to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "And Joseph called the name of the firstborn Manasseh, for he said,
        \u201CGod has caused me to forget all my hardship and all my father\u2019s
        house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "And the name of the second he called Ephraim, for he said, \u201CGod
        has made me fruitful in the land of my misfortune.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And the seven years of abundance which were in the land of Egypt
        came to an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'And the seven years of famine began to come as Joseph had said. And
        there was famine in all of the countries, but in the land of Egypt there
        was food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "And when all the land of Egypt was hungry the people cried out to
        Pharaoh for food. And Pharaoh said to all the land of Egypt, \u201CGo to
        Joseph; what he says to you, you must do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'And the famine was over the whole land, and Joseph opened all the
        storehouses and sold food to the Egyptians. And the famine was severe in
        the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'And every land came to Egypt to Joseph to buy grain, for the famine
        was severe in every land. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Brothers Go to Egypt for Food"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Brothers Go to Egypt for Food"
      number: 1
      content: "When Jacob realized that there was grain in Egypt, Jacob said to
        his sons, \u201CWhy do you look at one another?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLook, I have heard that there is grain in Egypt.
        Go down there and buy grain for us there that we may live and not die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the ten brothers of Joseph went down to buy grain from Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Jacob did not send Benjamin, the brother of Joseph, for he feared
        harm would come to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the sons of Israel went to buy grain amid those other people
        who went as well, for there was famine in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now Joseph was the governor over the land. He was the one who sold
        food to all the people of the land. And the brothers of Joseph came and bowed
        down to him with their faces to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Joseph saw his brothers and recognized them, but he pretended
        to be a stranger to them. And he spoke with them harshly and said to them,
        \u201CFrom where have you come?\u201D And they said, \u201CFrom the land
        of Canaan to buy food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Joseph recognized his brothers, but they did not recognize him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Joseph remembered the dreams which he had dreamed concerning
        them, and he said to them, \u201CYou are spies! You have come to see the
        nakedness of the land!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CNo, my lord, but your servants have come
        to buy food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "We all are sons of one man. We are honest men. We, your servants,
        are not spies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CNo, but you have come to see the nakedness
        of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then they said, \u201CWe, your servants, are twelve brothers, the
        sons of one man in the land of Canaan, but behold, the youngest is with our
        father today, and one is no more.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Joseph said to them, \u201CIt is what I said to you\u2014you
        are spies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'By this you shall be tested. By the life of Pharaoh you will not
        go out from here unless your youngest brother comes here. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Send one of you, and let him bring your brother, but you will be
        kept in prison so that your words might be tested to see if there is truth
        with you. And if not, by the life of Pharaoh surely you are spies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then he gathered them into the prison for three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On the third day Joseph said to them, \u201CDo this and you will
        live; I fear God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If you are honest, let one of your brothers be kept in prison where
        you are now being kept, but the rest of you go, carry grain for the famine
        for your households. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You must bring your youngest brother to me, and then your words will
        be confirmed and you will not die.\u201D And they did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then each said to his brother, \u201CSurely we are guilty on account
        of our brother when we saw the anguish of his soul when he pleaded for mercy
        to us and we would not listen. Therefore this trouble has come to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Reuben answered them, saying, \u201CDid I not say to you, do
        not sin against the boy? But you did not listen, and now, behold, his blood
        has been sought.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now they did not know that Joseph understood, for the interpreter
        was between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he turned away from them and wept. Then he returned to them and
        spoke to them, and took Simeon from them and tied him up in front of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Joseph gave orders to fill their bags with grain and to return
        their money to each sack, and to give them provisions for the journey. Thus
        he did for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then they loaded their grain upon their donkeys and went away from
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And one of them later opened his sack to give fodder to his donkey
        at the lodging place and saw his money\u2014behold, it was in the mouth of
        his sack. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said to his brothers, \u201CMy money was returned and moreover,
        behold, it is in my sack!\u201D Then their hearts failed them and each of
        them trembled and said, \u201CWhat is this God has done to us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when they came to Jacob their father in the land of Canaan they
        told him everything that had happened to them, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThe man, the lord of the land, spoke harshly to us and treated
        us as if we were spying out the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But we said to him, \u2018We are honest; we are not spies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "We are twelve brothers, the sons of our father. One is no more and
        the youngest is with our father now in the land of Canaan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then the man, the lord of the land, said to us, \u2018By this I will
        know that you are honest. Leave one brother with me, and take food for the
        famine in your households and go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And bring your youngest brother to me. Then I will know that you
        are not spies but you are honest. And I will give your brother back to you,
        and you will trade in the land.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And it happened that when they emptied their sacks, behold, each
        one\u2019s pouch of money was in his sack. And when they and their father
        saw the pouches of their money, they were greatly distressed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Jacob their father said to them, \u201CYou have bereaved me\u2014Joseph
        is no more and Simeon is no more, and Benjamin you would take! All of this
        is against me! "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Reuben said to his father, \u201CYou may kill my two sons if
        I do not bring him back to you. Put him in my hand and I myself will return
        him to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But he said, \u201CMy son shall not go down with you, for his brother
        is dead and he alone remains. If harm meets him on the journey that you would
        take, you would bring down my gray head in sorrow to Sheol.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Brothers Return to Egypt"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Brothers Return to Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the famine in the land was severe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it happened that as they finished eating the grain which they
        had brought from Egypt their father said to them, \u201CReturn and buy a
        little food for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Judah said to him, \u201CThe man solemnly admonished us, saying,
        \u2018You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If you will send our brother with us, we will go down and buy food
        for you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "but if you will not send him, we will not go down, for the man said
        to us, \u2018You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Israel said, \u201CWhy did you bring trouble to me by telling
        the man you still had a brother?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they said, \u201CThe man asked explicitly about us and about
        our family, saying, \u2018Is your father still alive? Do you have a brother?\u2019
        And we answered him according to these words. How could we know that he would
        say, \u2018Bring down your brother\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Judah said to his father Israel, \u201CSend the boy with me,
        and let us arise and go, so that we will live and not die\u2014you, we, and
        our children. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I myself will be surety for him. You may seek him from my hand. If
        I do not bring him back to you and present him before you, then I will stand
        guilty before you forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Surely if we had not hesitated by this time we would have returned
        twice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then their father Israel said to them, \u201CIf it must be so then
        do this. Take some of the best products of the land in your bags and take
        them down to the man as a gift\u2014a little balm and honey, aromatic gum
        and myrrh, and pistachios and almonds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And take double the money in your hands. Take back the money that
        was returned in the mouth of your sacks. Perhaps it was a mistake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And take your brother. Now arise and return to the man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And may El-Shaddai grant you compassion before the man that he may
        release your other brother to you and Benjamin. As for me, if I am bereaved,
        I am bereaved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the men took this gift, and they took double money in their hands,
        and Benjamin, and they rose up and went down to Egypt and stood before Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Joseph saw Benjamin with them he said to the one who was over
        his household, \u201CBring the men into the house and slaughter and prepare
        an animal, for the men shall eat with me at noon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the man did as Joseph had said, and the man brought the men into
        the house of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the men were afraid when they were brought into the house of
        Joseph. And they said \u201CWe were brought here on account of the money
        that was returned to our sacks the first time, that he might attack us and
        fall upon us to take us as slaves with our donkeys.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So they approached the man who was over Joseph\u2019s house and spoke
        to him at the doorway of the house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And they said, \u201CPlease, my lord, we surely came down once before
        to buy food, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but when we came to the place of lodging and we opened our sacks,
        then behold, each one\u2019s money was in the mouth of his sack\u2014our
        money in its full weight\u2014so we have returned with it in our hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now, other money we have brought down in our hand to buy food. We
        do not know who put our money in our sacks.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he said, \u201CPeace to you; do not be afraid. Your God and the
        God of your father must have given you a treasure in your sacks; your money
        came to me.\u201D And he brought Simeon out to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the man brought the men into Joseph\u2019s house and he gave
        them water and washed their feet, and gave fodder to their donkeys. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they laid out the gift until Joseph came at noon, for they had
        heard that they were to eat food there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when Joseph came into the house they brought the gift that was
        in their hand into the house to him, and they bowed down before him to the
        ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he greeted them and said, \u201CIs your father well, the old
        man of whom you spoke? Is he still alive?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And they said, \u201CYour servant our father is well; he is still
        alive.\u201D And they knelt and bowed down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he lifted up his eyes and saw Benjamin his brother, the son
        of his mother, and said, \u201CIs this your youngest brother of whom you
        told me?\u201D And he continued, \u201CGod be gracious to you, my son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Joseph hurried away, being overcome with emotion toward his
        brother, and sought for a place to cry. Then he went into a room and wept
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he washed his face and went out, now controlling himself, and
        said, \u201CServe the food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And they served him by himself, and them by themselves, and the Egyptians
        who were eating with him by themselves, for Egyptians could not dine with
        Hebrews, because that was a detestable thing to Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they were seated before him from the firstborn according to his
        birthright to the youngest according to his youth. And the men looked at
        one another amazed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And portions were served to them from his table, and the portion
        of Benjamin was five times greater than the portion of any of them. And they
        drank and became drunk with him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Tests His Brothers'
      title: Joseph Tests His Brothers
      number: 1
      content: "Then he commanded the one who was over his household, saying, \u201CFill
        the sacks of the men with food as much as they are able to carry, and put
        each one\u2019s money in the mouth of his sack. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And my cup\u2014the cup of silver\u2014you shall put into the mouth
        of the sack of the youngest, and the money for his grain. And he did according
        to the word of Joseph that he had commanded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When the morning light came the men were sent away, they and their
        donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They went out of the city, and had not gone far when Joseph said
        to the one who was over his house, \u201CArise! Pursue after the men and
        overtake them. Then you shall say to them, \u2018Why have you repaid evil
        for good? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is this not that from which my master drinks? Now he himself certainly
        practices divination with it. You have done evil in what you have done.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When he overtook them he spoke these words to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWhy has my lord spoken according to these
        words? Far be it from your servants to do such a thing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Behold, the money that we found in the mouth of our sacks we returned
        to you from the land of Canaan. Now why would we steal silver or gold from
        the house of my lord? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Whoever is found with it from among your servants shall die. And
        moreover, we will become slaves to my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said, \u201CNow also according to your words, thus will it
        be. He who is found with it shall be my slave, but you shall be innocent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then each man quickly brought down his sack to the ground, and each
        one opened his sack. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he searched, beginning with the oldest and finishing with the
        youngest. And the cup was found in the sack of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they tore their clothes, and each one loaded his donkey and
        they returned to the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Judah and his brothers came to the house of Joseph\u2014now he
        was still there\u2014they fell before him to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Joseph said to them, \u201CWhat is this deed that you have done?
        Did you not know that a man who is like me surely practices divination?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Judah said, \u201CWhat can we say to my lord? What can we speak?
        Now how can we show ourselves innocent? God has found the guilt of your servants!
        Behold, we are slaves to my lord, both we and also he in whose hand the cup
        was found.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But he said, \u201CFar be it from me to do this! The man in whose
        hand the cup was found, he will become my slave. But as for you, go up in
        peace to your father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But Judah drew near to him and said, \u201CPlease my lord, let your
        servant speak a word in the ears of my lord, and let not your anger burn
        against your servant, for you are like Pharaoh himself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "My lord had asked his servants, saying, \u2018Do you have a father
        or a brother?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And we said to my lord, \u2018We have an aged father, and a younger
        brother, the child of his old age, and his brother died, and he alone remains
        from his mother, and his father loves him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you said to your servants, \u2018Bring him down to me that I
        may set my eyes upon him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then we said to my lord, \u2018The boy cannot leave his father; if
        he should leave his father, then he would die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then you said to your servants, \u2018Unless your youngest brother
        comes down with you, you shall not again see my face.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And it happened that we went up to your servant, my father, and told
        him the words of my lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And when our father said, \u2018Buy a little food for us,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then we said, \u2018We cannot go down. If our youngest brother is
        with us, then we shall go down. For we will not be able to see the face of
        the man unless our youngest brother is with us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then your servant, my father, said to us, \u2018You yourselves know
        that my wife bore two sons to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "One went out from me, and I said, \u201CSurely he must have been
        torn to pieces,\u201D and I have never seen him since. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And if you take this one also from me, and he encounters harm, you
        will bring down my gray head in sorrow to Sheol.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So now, when I come to your servant, my father, and the boy is not
        with us\u2014now his life is bound up with his life\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'it shall happen that when he sees that the boy is gone, he will die.
        And your servants will bring down the gray head of your servant, our father,
        to Sheol with sorrow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For your servant is pledged as surety for the boy by my father, saying,
        If I do not bring him to you, then I shall be culpable to my father forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So then, please let your servant remain in place of the boy as a
        slave to my lord, and let the boy go up with his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For how can I go up to my father if the boy is not with me? I do
        not want to see the misery which will find my father.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Reveals His Identity'
      title: Joseph Reveals His Identity
      number: 1
      content: "Then Joseph was not able to control himself before all who were standing
        by him. And he cried out, \u201CMake every man go out from me!\u201D So no
        one stood with him when Joseph made himself known to his brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he wept loudly, so that the Egyptians heard it and the household
        of Pharaoh heard it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CI am Joseph! Is my father
        still alive?\u201D And his brothers were unable to answer him, for they were
        dismayed at his presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CCome near to me, please.\u201D
        And they drew near. And he said, \u201CI am Joseph, your brother, whom you
        sold into Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So now, do not be distressed and do not be angry with yourselves
        that you sold me here, for God sent me as deliverance before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For these two years the famine has been in the midst of the land,
        but there will be five more years where there is no plowing or harvest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And God sent me before you all to preserve for you a remnant in the
        land and to keep alive among you many survivors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So now, you yourselves did not send me here, but God put me here
        as father to Pharaoh and as master of all his household, and a ruler over
        all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Hurry, and go up to my father and say to him, \u2018Thus says your
        son Joseph, God has made me lord of all Egypt. Come down to me and do not
        delay. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall settle in the land of Goshen so that you will be near me,
        you and your children and your grandchildren, and your flocks and your herds
        and all that you have. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And I will provide for you there, because there are still five years
        of famine\u2014lest you and your household and all that you have become destitute.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now behold, your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin see,
        that it is I who am speaking to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And you must tell my father of all my honor in Egypt and all that
        you have seen. Now hurry and bring my father here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then he fell upon the neck of his brother Benjamin and wept, and
        Benjamin wept upon his neck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he kissed all his brothers and wept upon them. And afterward
        his brothers spoke with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the report was heard in the house of Pharaoh, saying, \u201CJoseph\u2019s
        brothers have come.\u201D And it pleased Pharaoh and his servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSay to your brothers: \u2018Do
        this\u2014load your donkeys and go back to the land of Canaan, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and take your father and your households and come to me, and I will
        give you the best of the land of Egypt, and you shall eat the fat of the
        land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And you Joseph, are commanded to say this: \u2018Do this! Take wagons
        from the land of Egypt for your little ones and your wives, and bring your
        father and come! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Do not worry about your possessions, for the best of all the land
        of Egypt is yours.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the sons of Israel did so. And Joseph gave them wagons at the
        word of Pharaoh, and gave them provisions for the journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'To each and to all of them he gave sets of clothing, but to Benjamin
        he gave three hundred pieces of silver and five sets of clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And to his father he sent as follows: ten donkeys carrying the best
        of Egypt, and ten donkeys carrying grain and food and provisions for his
        father for the journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then he sent his brothers away, and when they departed he said to
        them, \u201CDo not be agitated on the journey.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So they went up from Egypt and came to the land of Canaan to Jacob
        their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they spoke to him, saying, \u201CJoseph is still alive, and he
        is ruler over all the land of Egypt.\u201D And his heart went numb, because
        he did not believe him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then they told him all the words of Joseph that he had spoken to
        them. And when he saw the wagons that Joseph had sent to carry him, then
        the spirit of Jacob their father revived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Israel said, \u201CIt is enough. Joseph my son is still alive.
        I will go and see him before I die.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob and His Offspring Go to Egypt'
      title: Jacob and His Offspring Go to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'So Israel journeyed with all that he had, and he came to Beersheba
        and offered sacrifices to the God of his father, Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And God spoke to Israel in visions of the night and said, \u201CJacob,
        Jacob.\u201D And he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI am the God of your father. Do not be afraid
        to go down to Egypt, for I will make you a great nation there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I myself will go down with you to Egypt, and I myself will also bring
        you up. And Joseph will place his hand over your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Jacob arose from Beersheba. And the sons of Israel carried their
        father Jacob, and their little ones and their wives in the wagons Pharaoh
        had sent to transport him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And they took their livestock and their possessions that they had
        acquired in the land of Canaan. And they came to Egypt, Jacob and all his
        offspring with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "his sons and his sons\u2019 sons with him, his daughters and his
        daughters\u2019 daughters with him, into Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now these are the names of the sons of Israel, who came into Egypt,
        Jacob and his sons. Reuben, the firstborn of Jacob '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and the sons of Reuben: Enoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The sons of Simeon: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jakin, Zohar, and Shaul,
        the son of a Canaanite woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Judah: Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah (but Er and
        Onan died in the land of Canaan). And the sons of Perez were Hezron and Hamul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Issachar: Tolah, Puvah, Iob, and Shimron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of Zebulun: Sered, Elon, and Jahleel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the sons of Leah that she bore to Jacob in Paddan-Aram,
        and Dinah his daughter. His sons and daughters were thirty-three persons
        in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Gad: Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and Areli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, and Beriah, and their sister
        Serah. And the sons of Beriah: Heber and Malkiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "There are the sons of Zilpah, whom Laban gave to Leah his daughter,
        and she bore these to Jacob\u2014sixteen persons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The sons of Rachel, Jacob\u2019s wife: Joseph and Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Ephraim and Manasseh, whom Asenath, daughter of Potiphera, priest
        of On bore to him, were born to Joseph in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Benjamin: Bela, Beker, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi, Rosh,
        Muppim, Huppim, and Ard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "These are the sons of Rachel who were born to Jacob\u2014fourteen
        persons in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Dan: Hushim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Naphtali: Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "These are the sons of Bilhah whom Laban gave to Rachel his daughter,
        and she bore these to Jacob\u2014seven persons in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'All the persons belonging to Jacob who came to Egypt who were his
        descendants, not including the wives of the sons of Jacob were sixty-six
        persons in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the sons of Joseph who were born to him in Egypt were two persons.
        All the persons of the house of Jacob who came to Egypt were seventy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He had sent Judah ahead of him to Joseph to appear before him in
        Goshen. And they came to the land of Goshen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Joseph harnessed his chariot and went up to meet Israel his
        father in Goshen. He presented himself to him and fell upon his neck and
        wept upon his neck a long time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Israel said to Joseph, \u201CNow let me die since I have seen
        your face, for you are still alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Joseph said to his brothers and to his father\u2019s household,
        \u201CI will go up and report to Pharaoh, and I will say to him, \u2018My
        brothers and my father\u2019s household who were in the land of Canaan have
        come to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the men are shepherds, for they are men of livestock, and they
        have brought their flocks and their cattle and all that they have.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And it shall be that when Pharaoh calls you he will say, \u2018What
        is your occupation?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then you must say, \u2018You servants are men of livestock from our
        childhood until now, both we and also our ancestors,\u2019 so that you may
        dwell in the land of Goshen, for every shepherd is a detestable thing to
        Egyptians.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Settles in Goshen'
      title: Jacob Settles in Goshen
      number: 1
      content: "So Joseph went and reported to Pharaoh. And he said, \u201CMy father
        and my brothers, with their flocks and their herds, and all that they have,
        have come from the land of Canaan. Now they are here in the land of Goshen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And from among his brothers he took five men and presented them before
        Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Pharaoh said to his brothers, \u201CWhat is your occupation?\u201D
        And they said to Pharaoh, \u201CYour servants are keepers of sheep, both
        we and also our ancestors.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they said to Pharaoh, \u201CWe have come to sojourn in the land,
        for there is no pasture for your servant\u2019s flocks, for the famine is
        severe in the land of Canaan. So now, please let your servants dwell in the
        land of Goshen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CYour father and your brothers
        have come to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The land of Egypt is before you. Settle your father and your brothers
        in the best of the land. Let them live in the land of Goshen, and if you
        know there is among them men of ability, then appoint them overseers of my
        own livestock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Joseph brought his father Jacob and presented him before Pharaoh.
        And Jacob blessed Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Jacob, \u201CHow old are you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jacob said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe days of the years of my sojourning
        are one hundred and thirty years. Few and hard have been the days of the
        years of my life, and they have not reached the days of the years of the
        lives of my ancestors in the days of their sojourning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and he went out from the presence of Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Joseph settled his father and his brothers, and he gave them
        property in the land of Egypt in the best part of the land, in the land of
        Rameses, as Pharaoh had instructed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Famine in Egypt Continues'
      title: The Famine in Egypt Continues
      number: 12
      content: 'And Joseph provided his father and his brothers and all the household
        of his father with food, according to the number of their children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now there was no food in all the land, for the famine was very severe.
        And the land of Egypt languished, with the land of Canaan, on account of
        the famine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Joseph collected all the money found in the land of Egypt and
        in the land of Canaan in exchange for the grain that they were buying. And
        Joseph brought the money into the house of Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when the money was spent in the land of Egypt and from the land
        of Canaan, all of Egypt came to Joseph, saying, \u201CGive us food! Why should
        we die before you? For the money is used up.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Joseph said, \u201CGive your livestock and I will give you food
        in exchange for your livestock if your money is used up.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So they brought their herds to Joseph, and Joseph gave food to them
        in exchange for horses, their flocks, and their cattle and donkeys. And he
        provided them with food in exchange for all their livestock that year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When that year ended, they came to him in the following year and
        said to him, \u201CWe cannot hide from my lord that our money and livestock
        belong to my lord. Nothing remains before my lord except our bodies and our
        land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why should we die in front of you, both we and our land? Buy us and
        our land in exchange for food, then we and our land will be servants to Pharaoh.
        Then give us seed and we shall live and not die, and the land will not become
        desolate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh, for each Egyptian
        sold his field, for the famine was severe upon them. And the land became
        Pharaoh\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As for the people, he transferred them to the cities, from one end
        of the territory of Egypt to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Only the land of the priests he did not buy, for there was an allotment
        for the priests from Pharaoh, and they lived on the allotment that Pharaoh
        gave to them. Therefore they did not sell their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Joseph said to the people, \u201CLook, I have bought you and
        your land this day for Pharaoh. Here is seed for you so you can sow the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And it shall happen that at the harvest, you must give a fifth to
        Pharaoh and four-fifths shall be yours, as seed for the field and for your
        food and for those who are in your households, and as food for your little
        ones.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And they said, \u201CYou have saved our lives. If we have found favor
        in the eyes of my lord, we will be servants to Pharaoh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So Joseph made it a statute unto this day concerning the land of
        Egypt: one fifth to Pharaoh. Only the land of the priests alone did not belong
        to Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Israel settled in the land of Egypt, in the land of Goshen. And
        they acquired possessions in it and were fruitful and multiplied greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years. And the days
        of Jacob, the years of his life, were one hundred and forty-seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When the time of Israel\u2019s death drew near, he called to his
        son, to Joseph. And he said to him, \u201CIf I have found favor in your eyes,
        please put your hand under my thigh, that you might vow to deal kindly and
        faithfully with me. Please do not bury me in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "but let me lie with my ancestors. Carry me out of Egypt and bury
        me in their burial site.\u201D And he said, \u201CI will do according to
        your word.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he said, \u201CSwear to me.\u201D And he swore to him. Then
        Israel bowed himself on the head of the bed. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Blesses Ephraim and Manasseh'
      title: Jacob Blesses Ephraim and Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: "And it happened that after these things, it was said to Joseph, \u201CBehold,
        your father is ill.\u201D And he took his two sons with him, Ephraim and
        Manasseh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it was told to Jacob, \u201CBehold, your son Joseph has come
        to you.\u201D Then Israel strengthened himself and he sat up in the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Jacob said to Joseph, \u201CEl-Shaddai appeared to me in Luz,
        in the land of Canaan, and blessed me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and said to me, \u2018Behold, I will make you fruitful and make you
        numerous, and will make you a company of nations. And I will give this land
        to your offspring after you as an everlasting possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now, your two sons who were born to you in the land of Egypt
        before my coming to you in Egypt, are mine. Ephraim and Manasseh shall be
        mine as Reuben and Simeon are. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And your children whom you father after them shall be yours. By the
        name of their brothers they shall be called, with respect to their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As for me, when I came to Paddan-Aram Rachel died to my sorrow in
        the land of Canaan on the way when there was still some distance to go to
        Ephrath. And I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When Israel saw the sons of Joseph he said, \u201CWho are these?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Joseph said to his father, \u201CThey are my sons whom God has
        given me here.\u201D And he said, \u201CPlease bring them to me that I may
        bless them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the eyes of Israel were dim on account of old age; he was not
        able to see. So he brought them near to him, and he kissed them and embraced
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CI did not expect to see your face
        and behold, God has also shown me your offspring.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Joseph removed them from his knees and bowed down with his face
        to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Joseph took the two of them, Ephraim at his right to the left
        of Israel, and Manasseh at his left to the right of Israel. And he brought
        them near to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Israel stretched out his right hand and put it on the head of
        Ephraim (now he was the younger), and his left hand on the head of Manasseh,
        crossing his hands, for Manasseh was the firstborn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he blessed Joseph and said, \u201CThe God before whom my fathers,
        Abraham and Isaac, walked, The God who shepherded me all my life unto this
        day, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The angel who redeemed me from all evil, may he bless the boys. And
        through them let my name be perpetuated,  and the name of my fathers, Abraham
        and Isaac. And let them multiply into many in the midst of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Joseph saw that his father put his right hand on the head of
        Ephraim, he was displeased. And he took hold of his father\u2019s hand to
        remove it from the head of Ephraim over to the head of Manasseh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Joseph said to his father, \u201CNot so, my father; because this
        one is the firstborn. Put your right hand upon his head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But his father refused and said, \u201CI know, my son; I know. He
        also shall become a people, and he also shall be great, but his younger brother
        shall be greater than him, and his offspring shall become a multitude of
        nations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So he blessed them that day, saying, Through you Israel shall pronounce
        blessing, saying, \u2018May God make you like Ephraim and like Manasseh.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        So he put Ephraim before Manasseh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CBehold, I am about to die, but God
        will be with you and will bring you back to the land of your ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And I have given to you one slope of land rather than your brothers,
        which I took from the hand of the Amorites by my sword and with my bow.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Blesses His Twelve Sons'
      title: Jacob Blesses His Twelve Sons
      number: 1
      content: "Then Jacob called his sons and said, \u201CGather together so that
        I can tell you what will happen with you in days to come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Assemble and hear, O sons of Jacob! Listen to Israel your father! '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Reuben, you are my firstborn, my strength, and the firstfruit of
        my vigor, excelling in rank and excelling in power. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Unstable as water, you shall not excel any longer, for you went up
        upon the bed of your father, then defiled it. You went up upon my couch! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Simeon and Levi are brothers; weapons of violence are their swords.
        Let me not come into their council. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Let not my person be joined to their company. For in their anger
        they killed men, and at their pleasure they hamstrung cattle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Cursed be their anger, for it is fierce, and their wrath, for it
        is cruel. I will divide them in Jacob, and I will scatter them in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Judah, as for you, your brothers shall praise you. Your hand shall
        be on the neck of your enemies. The sons of your father shall bow down to
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Judah is a lion\u2019s cub. From the prey, my son, you have gone
        up. He bowed down; he crouched like a lion and as a lioness. Who shall rouse
        him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The scepter shall not depart from Judah, nor the ruler\u2019s staff
        between his feet, until Shiloh comes. And to him shall be the obedience of
        nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Binding his donkey to the vine and his donkey\u2019s colt to the
        choice vine, he washes his clothing in the wine and his garment in the blood
        of grapes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The eyes are darker than wine, and the teeth whiter than milk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Zebulun shall settle by the shore of the sea. He shall become a haven
        for ships, and his border shall be at Sidon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Issachar is a strong donkey, crouching between the sheepfolds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He saw a resting place that was good, and land that was pleasant.
        So he bowed his shoulder to the burden and became a servant of forced labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Dan shall judge his people as one of the tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Dan shall be a serpent on the way, a viper on the road that bites
        the heels of a horse, so that its rider falls backward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I wait for your salvation, O Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Bandits shall attack Gad, but he shall attack their heels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Asher\u2019s food is delicious, and he shall provide from the king\u2019s
        delicacies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Naphtali is a doe running free that puts forth beautiful words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Joseph is the bough of a fruitful vine, a fruitful bough by a spring.
        His branches climb over the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The archers fiercely attacked him. They shot arrows at him and were
        hostile to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But his bow remained in a steady position; his arms were made agile
        by the hands of the Mighty One of Jacob. From there is the Shepherd, the
        Rock of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Because of the God of your father he will help you and by Shaddai
        he will bless you with the blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep
        that crouches beneath, blessings of the breasts and the womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The blessings of your father are superior to the blessings of my
        ancestors, to the bounty of the everlasting hills. May they be on the head
        of Joseph, and on the forehead of the prince of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Death and Burial of Jacob'
      title: The Death and Burial of Jacob
      number: 27
      content: 'Benjamin is a devouring wolf, devouring the prey in the morning,
        and dividing the plunder in the evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'All these are the twelve tribes of Israel, and this is what their
        father said to them when he blessed them, each according to their blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he instructed them and said to them, \u201CI am about to be
        gathered to my people. Bury me among my ancestors in the cave that is in
        the field of Ephron the Hittite, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'in the cave that is in the field of Machpelah that is before Mamre
        in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field from Ephron the
        Hittite as a burial site. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife. There they buried Isaac
        and Rebekah his wife. And there I buried Leah\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "the purchase of the field and the cave which was in it from the Hittites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When Jacob finished instructing his sons he drew his feet up to the
        bed. Then he took his last breath and was gathered to his people. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Funeral and Joseph\u2019s Remaining Time in Egypt"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Funeral and Joseph\u2019s Remaining Time in Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Joseph fell on the face of his father and wept upon him and
        kissed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Joseph instructed his servants the physicians to embalm his father.
        So the physicians embalmed Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Forty days were required for it, for thus are the days required for
        embalming. And the Egyptians wept for him seventy days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the days of his weeping had passed, Joseph spoke to the household
        of Pharaoh, saying, \u201CIf I have found favor in your eyes, please speak
        in the hearing of Pharaoh, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018My father made me swear, saying, \u201CBehold, I am about to
        die. In the tomb that I have hewed out for myself in the land of Canaan\u2014there
        you must bury me.\u201D So then, please let me go up and let me bury my father;
        then I will return.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Pharaoh said, \u201CGo up and bury your father as he made you
        swear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joseph went up to bury his father. And all the servants of Pharaoh,
        the elders of his household, and all the elders of the land of Egypt, went
        up with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'with all the household of Joseph, his brothers, and the household
        of his father. They left only their little children and their flocks and
        their herds in the land of Goshen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And there also went up with him chariots and horsemen. The company
        was very great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which was beyond the
        Jordan, they lamented there with a very great and sorrowful wailing. And
        he made a mourning ceremony for his father seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land, saw the mourning
        ceremony at the threshing floor of Atad they said, \u201CThis is a severe
        mourning for the Egyptians.\u201D Therefore its name was called Abel-Mizraim,
        which is beyond the Jordan."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus his sons did to him just as he had instructed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And his sons carried him to the land of Canaan and buried him in
        the cave of the field of Machpelah, which field Abraham had bought as a burial
        site from Ephron the Hittite before Mamre. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And after burying his father, Joseph returned to Egypt, he and his
        brothers and all who had gone up with him to bury his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when the brothers of Joseph saw that their father was dead, they
        said, \u201CIt may be that Joseph will hold a grudge against us and pay us
        back dearly for all the evil that we did to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they sent word to Joseph saying, \u201CYour father commanded us
        before his death, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThus you must say to Joseph, \u2018O, please now forgive the
        transgression of your brothers and their sin, for they did evil to you.\u2019
        So now, please forgive the transgression of the servants of the God of your
        father.\u201D And Joseph wept when they spoke to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then his brothers went also and fell before him and said, \u201CBehold,
        we are your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Joseph said to them, \u201CDo not be afraid, for am I in the
        place of God? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "As for you, you planned evil against me, but God planned it for good,
        in order to do this\u2014to keep many people alive\u2014as it is today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Death of Joseph'
      title: The Death of Joseph
      number: 21
      content: 'So then, do not be afraid. I myself will provide for you and your
        little ones. And he consoled them and spoke kindly to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Joseph remained in Egypt, he and the house of his father. And
        Joseph lived one hundred and ten years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Joseph saw Ephraim\u2019s children to the third generation. Moreover,
        the children of Makir, son of Manasseh, were born on the knees of Joseph. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CI am about to die, but God
        will certainly visit you and bring you up from this land to the land that
        he swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph made the sons of Israel swear an oath, saying, \u201CGod
        will surely visit you, and you shall bring up my bones from here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So Joseph died, being one hundred and ten years old. They embalmed
        him and he was placed in a coffin in Egypt. '
      comments: []
